searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Analytics","doc":"Analytics — admin-scoped overview and timeseries metrics.\n\nRequires an admin (`msk_a_` / `msk_p_`) key.","ref":"Miosa.Analytics.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Analytics","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_ADMIN_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, overview} = Miosa.Analytics.overview(client)\n    {:ok, ts} = Miosa.Analytics.timeseries(client, %{metric: \"computers\", period: \"7d\"})","ref":"Miosa.Analytics.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Analytics.overview/2","doc":"Get the platform analytics overview.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:period`, `:tenant_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Analytics.html#overview/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Analytics.timeseries/2","doc":"Get a timeseries for a metric over a period.\n\nCommon options: `:metric` (e.g. `\"computers\"`), `:period` (e.g. `\"7d\"`).\nAccepts any additional filters supported by the API.","ref":"Miosa.Analytics.html#timeseries/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.ApiKeys","doc":"API key management — programmatic CRUD for tenant API keys.\n\nThe plaintext token is returned **only at creation time**. Store it\nimmediately; the server only retains a hash.\n\nMutating calls (create) send an `Idempotency-Key` header automatically.","ref":"Miosa.ApiKeys.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.ApiKeys","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.ApiKeys.create(client, %{\n      name: \"ci-deploy\",\n      scopes: [\"computers:read\", \"computers:write\"]\n    })\n\n    # Store result[\"token\"] immediately — it will not be shown again.\n\n    {:ok, keys} = Miosa.ApiKeys.list(client)\n    :ok = Miosa.ApiKeys.delete(client, result[\"id\"])","ref":"Miosa.ApiKeys.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ApiKeys.create/2","doc":"Create an API key.\n\nRequired: `:name`. Optional: `:scopes` (list of scope strings), `:expires_at`,\n`:metadata`, `:idempotency_key`.\n\nThe response contains a one-time plaintext `:token` (or `\"key\"`). Store it\nimmediately; the server only keeps a hash.","ref":"Miosa.ApiKeys.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ApiKeys.delete/2","doc":"Revoke (delete) an API key by ID.","ref":"Miosa.ApiKeys.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ApiKeys.list/2","doc":"List API keys for the authenticated tenant.\n\nNote: The plaintext token is never returned by the list endpoint.\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.ApiKeys.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.AuditLog","doc":"Audit log — admin-scoped event stream.\n\nRequires an admin (`msk_a_` / `msk_p_`) key.","ref":"Miosa.AuditLog.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.AuditLog","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_ADMIN_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, events} = Miosa.AuditLog.list(client)\n    {:ok, filtered} = Miosa.AuditLog.list(client, %{action: \"computer.create\", limit: 50})","ref":"Miosa.AuditLog.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.AuditLog.list/2","doc":"List audit-log events.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:action`, `:limit`,\n`:cursor`, `:since`).","ref":"Miosa.AuditLog.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Benchmarks","doc":"Admin-triggered platform benchmark runs.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/admin/benchmarks/` and require an admin\ncredential (`msk_a_*` / `msk_p_*` or admin JWT). Available run kinds\ninclude `cold_boot`, `fleet_routing`, `concurrent_create`, and `full_e2e`.","ref":"Miosa.Benchmarks.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Benchmarks.cancel/2","doc":"Cancel a running benchmark (POST `/admin/benchmarks/:benchmark_id/cancel`).","ref":"Miosa.Benchmarks.html#cancel/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Benchmarks.compare/4","doc":"Compare two benchmark runs (POST `/admin/benchmarks/compare`).","ref":"Miosa.Benchmarks.html#compare/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Benchmarks.create/2","doc":"Start a new benchmark run (POST `/admin/benchmarks`).\n\nPass `kind:` and run-specific options. E.g.:\n\n    Miosa.Benchmarks.create(client, %{kind: \"cold_boot\", count: 10})","ref":"Miosa.Benchmarks.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Benchmarks.get/2","doc":"Get a benchmark run by ID (GET `/admin/benchmarks/:benchmark_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Benchmarks.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Benchmarks.list/2","doc":"List all benchmark runs (GET `/admin/benchmarks`).\n\nAccepts optional filter params (e.g. `%{kind: \"cold_boot\"}`).","ref":"Miosa.Benchmarks.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Benchmarks.samples/3","doc":"Return per-iteration timing samples for a benchmark run\n(GET `/admin/benchmarks/:benchmark_id/samples`).","ref":"Miosa.Benchmarks.html#samples/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.BuilderSessions","doc":"Builder UI session metadata — durable, cross-device Builder state.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/builder/sessions/` and accept `msk_*` API\nkeys or JWT. Builder sessions are `optimal_sessions` with\n`resource_type = \"sandbox\"` and `vm_context.template_type = \"miosa-sandbox\"`.","ref":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.delete/2","doc":"Delete a builder session (DELETE `/builder/sessions/:session_id`).","ref":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.get/2","doc":"Get a single builder session by ID.\n\nFalls back to filtering `list/2` since the platform router only exposes\nindex + title-update + delete.","ref":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.list/2","doc":"List builder sessions (GET `/builder/sessions`).","ref":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.BuilderSessions.list/2","doc":"* `:limit` — Maximum sessions to return. Defaults to `50`.\n  * Any extra key is forwarded as a query param.","ref":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.html#list/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.update_title/3","doc":"Update the title of a builder session\n(PATCH `/builder/sessions/:session_id/title`).","ref":"Miosa.BuilderSessions.html#update_title/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Channels","doc":"Notification channels — Slack, Discord, email, and per-channel enable/disable.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Channels","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, channels} = Miosa.Channels.list(client)\n    {:ok, channel} = Miosa.Channels.create(client, %{type: \"slack\", webhook_url: \"https://...\"})\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.Channels.enable(client, channel[\"id\"])","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.create/2","doc":"Create a new notification channel.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.delete/2","doc":"Delete a channel by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.disable/2","doc":"Disable a channel by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#disable/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.enable/2","doc":"Enable a channel by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#enable/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.get/2","doc":"Get a single channel by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.list/2","doc":"List all channels for the tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.list_notifications/1","doc":"Get notification preferences across all channels.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#list_notifications/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.update/3","doc":"Update a channel by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#update/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Channels.update_notifications/2","doc":"Update notification preferences.","ref":"Miosa.Channels.html#update_notifications/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter","doc":"Read-only views of the Optimal AI agent fleet.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/command-center/` and require a JWT or\n`msk_u_*` API key.","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter.agents/1","doc":"List all agents in the fleet (GET `/command-center/agents`).","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html#agents/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter.events/2","doc":"Stream live command-center events via SSE (GET `/command-center/events`).\n\n`callback` is invoked for each event map with keys `type` and `data`.\nReturns `:ok` when the stream closes or `{:error, reason}` on failure.","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html#events/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter.metrics/1","doc":"Get fleet-wide metrics snapshot (GET `/command-center/metrics`).","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html#metrics/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter.overview/1","doc":"Top-level fleet snapshot (GET `/command-center`).","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html#overview/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter.presets/1","doc":"List agent execution presets (GET `/command-center/presets`).","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html#presets/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter.running_agents/1","doc":"List currently running agents (GET `/command-center/agents/running`).","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html#running_agents/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CommandCenter.tiers/1","doc":"Get agent tier configuration (GET `/command-center/tiers`).","ref":"Miosa.CommandCenter.html#tiers/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Community","doc":"Community template and agent catalog with install and rate actions.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/community/` and require a JWT.","ref":"Miosa.Community.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Community.get_agent/2","doc":"Get a community agent by ID (GET `/community/agents/:agent_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Community.html#get_agent/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Community.get_template/2","doc":"Get a community template by ID (GET `/community/templates/:template_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Community.html#get_template/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Community.install_template/3","doc":"Install a community template into the caller's tenant\n(POST `/community/templates/:template_id/install`).","ref":"Miosa.Community.html#install_template/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Community.list_agents/2","doc":"List community agents (GET `/community/agents`).\n\nAccepts optional filter params.","ref":"Miosa.Community.html#list_agents/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Community.list_templates/2","doc":"List community templates (GET `/community/templates`).\n\nAccepts optional filter params.","ref":"Miosa.Community.html#list_templates/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Community.rate_template/4","doc":"Rate a community template 1-5 (POST `/community/templates/:template_id/rate`).","ref":"Miosa.Community.html#rate_template/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Completions","doc":"OpenAI-compatible chat and text completion endpoints.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/intelligence/` and require an `mki_*`\nintelligence key. Streaming endpoints call `callback` for each SSE event.","ref":"Miosa.Completions.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Completions.chat/5","doc":"Create a chat completion (POST `/intelligence/chat/completions`).","ref":"Miosa.Completions.html#chat/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Miosa.Completions.chat/5","doc":"* `model` — Model ID string.\n  * `messages` — List of message maps (`%{\"role\" => ..., \"content\" => ...}`).\n  * `opts` — Optional extra body params (`:temperature`, `:max_tokens`, etc.).\n  * `callback` — Required when `opts.stream == true`. Called with each SSE event map.\n\nWhen `:stream` is `false` (default), returns `{:ok, response_map}`.","ref":"Miosa.Completions.html#chat/5-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Completions.create/4","doc":"Create a text completion (POST `/intelligence/completions`).","ref":"Miosa.Completions.html#create/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Completions.create/4","doc":"* `:stream` — When `true`, streams SSE events via `callback`. Defaults to `false`.\n  * `:prompt` — Text prompt (string or list of strings).\n  * Any extra key is forwarded to the API body.\n\nWhen `:stream` is `false`, returns `{:ok, response_map}`.\nWhen `:stream` is `true`, pass a `callback` function; returns `:ok` or `{:error, reason}`.","ref":"Miosa.Completions.html#create/4-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.AutoStop","doc":"Read and update idle-timeout config for a computer.\n\nMaps to `GET /computers/:id/auto-stop` and `PATCH /computers/:id/auto-stop`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.AutoStop.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.AutoStop.get/2","doc":"Return the current auto-stop configuration\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/auto-stop`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.AutoStop.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.AutoStop.update/3","doc":"Set the idle timeout in seconds (PATCH `/computers/:computer_id/auto-stop`).\n\nPass `0` to disable auto-stop entirely.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.AutoStop.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Env","doc":"Encrypted env-var CRUD scoped to one computer.\n\n  * `GET    /computers/:id/env`          — list/2\n  * `POST   /computers/:id/env`          — set/4\n  * `PATCH  /computers/:id/env/:name`    — update/4\n  * `DELETE /computers/:id/env/:name`    — delete/3\n  * `bulk_set/3` — convenience wrapper over set/4","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Env.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Env.bulk_set/3","doc":"Convenience: create one env var per entry in `env` map.\n\nFalls back to N individual `set/4` calls (no bulk backend endpoint yet).\nReturns a list of results in the same order as `Map.to_list(env)`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Env.html#bulk_set/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Env.delete/3","doc":"Delete an env var by name (DELETE `/computers/:computer_id/env/:name`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Env.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Env.list/2","doc":"List all env vars for a computer (GET `/computers/:computer_id/env`).\n\nValues may be masked depending on server policy.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Env.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Env.set/4","doc":"Create a new env var (POST `/computers/:computer_id/env`).\n\nUse `update/4` to change an existing one.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Env.html#set/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Env.update/4","doc":"Patch the value of an existing env var (PATCH `/computers/:computer_id/env/:name`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Env.html#update/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Inbox","doc":"Per-computer inbox configuration for Optimal inbound-email routing.\n\nMaps to `GET /computers/:id/inbox` and `PATCH /computers/:id/inbox`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Inbox.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Inbox.get/2","doc":"Fetch the current inbox configuration (GET `/computers/:computer_id/inbox`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Inbox.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Inbox.update/3","doc":"Patch one or more inbox fields (PATCH `/computers/:computer_id/inbox`).\n\nCommon fields: `alias`, `enabled`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Inbox.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Logs","doc":"Read and stream VM logs for a computer.\n\n  * `GET /computers/:id/logs`         — snapshot (JSON)\n  * `GET /computers/:id/logs/stream`  — live SSE stream","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Logs.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Logs.get/3","doc":"Fetch the most recent log snapshot (GET `/computers/:computer_id/logs`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Logs.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Computer.Logs.get/3","doc":"* `:lines` — Number of log lines to return.\n  * `:since` — ISO8601 timestamp; return only lines after this time.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Logs.html#get/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Logs.stream/3","doc":"Stream live log events via SSE (GET `/computers/:computer_id/logs/stream`).\n\n`callback` is called for each event map `%{type: ..., data: ...}`.\nReturns `:ok` when the stream closes or `{:error, reason}` on failure.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Logs.html#stream/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Metrics","doc":"Time-series RAM/CPU/credit metrics for a computer.\n\nMaps to `GET /computers/:id/metrics`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Metrics.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Metrics.get/3","doc":"Return metric series for a time window\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/metrics`).\n\n`window` is a duration string such as `\"1h\"`, `\"24h\"`, or `\"7d\"`.\nDefaults to `\"1h\"`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Metrics.html#get/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Osa","doc":"Task dispatch to the in-VM OSA agent.\n\nWraps:\n  * `POST   /computers/:id/osa/task`      — submit_task/3\n  * `DELETE /computers/:id/osa/task`      — cancel_task/2\n  * `GET    /computers/:id/osa/status`    — status/2\n  * `POST   /computers/:id/osa/configure` — configure/3","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.cancel_task/2","doc":"Cancel the currently-running OSA task, if any\n(DELETE `/computers/:computer_id/osa/task`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.html#cancel_task/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.configure/3","doc":"Update OSA runtime configuration — model, tools, secrets, etc.\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/osa/configure`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.html#configure/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.status/2","doc":"Return OSA's current task, configuration, and health snapshot\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/osa/status`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.html#status/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.submit_task/4","doc":"Submit a free-form task to the in-VM OSA agent\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/osa/task`).\n\nAdditional params are merged into the request body.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Osa.html#submit_task/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Ports","doc":"Per-port visibility control for a computer.\n\n  * `GET    /computers/:id/ports`          — list/2\n  * `POST   /computers/:id/ports`          — create/3\n  * `PATCH  /computers/:id/ports/:port`    — update/4\n  * `DELETE /computers/:id/ports/:port`    — delete/3\n\nThe backend does not expose a single-port GET; `get/3` filters\nthe list response client-side.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.create/4","doc":"Expose a port with the given visibility options\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/ports`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.html#create/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.delete/3","doc":"Stop exposing a port (DELETE `/computers/:computer_id/ports/:port`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.get/3","doc":"Return the port record for `port`, or `{:ok, nil}` if not exposed.\n\nFilters `list/2` client-side.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.list/2","doc":"List all exposed ports (GET `/computers/:computer_id/ports`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.update/4","doc":"Patch visibility/auth options for a port\n(PATCH `/computers/:computer_id/ports/:port`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Ports.html#update/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Terminal","doc":"PTY session management for a computer.\n\nMaps to `POST /computers/:id/terminal` (create) and\n`POST /computers/:id/pty/:session_id/resize` (resize).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Terminal.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Terminal.create/3","doc":"Open a new PTY session (POST `/computers/:computer_id/terminal`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Terminal.html#create/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Computer.Terminal.create/3","doc":"* `:cols` — Terminal column width.\n  * `:rows` — Terminal row count.\n  * `:shell` — Shell binary path (e.g. `\"/bin/bash\"`).\n  * `:cwd` — Working directory inside the VM.\n  * `:env` — Environment variables map.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Terminal.html#create/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Terminal.resize/5","doc":"Resize an existing PTY session\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/pty/:session_id/resize`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Terminal.html#resize/5"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes","doc":"Per-computer volume attachment management.\n\n  * `GET    /computers/:id/volumes`          — list/2\n  * `POST   /computers/:id/volumes`          — attach/4\n  * `DELETE /computers/:id/volumes/:aid`     — detach/3","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes.attach/4","doc":"Attach a volume at `mount_path` inside the VM\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/volumes`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes.html#attach/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes.detach/3","doc":"Detach a volume attachment by attachment ID\n(DELETE `/computers/:computer_id/volumes/:attachment_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes.html#detach/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes.list/2","doc":"List volume attachments for a computer\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/volumes`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Volumes.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.CronJobs","doc":"Cron jobs — scheduled work with full CRUD, pause/resume, run-now, and\nexecution history.\n\nMutating calls (create, update, pause, resume, run_now) send an\n`Idempotency-Key` header automatically.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.CronJobs","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, job} = Miosa.CronJobs.create(client, %{\n      name: \"nightly-report\",\n      schedule: \"0 4 * * *\",\n      url: \"https://api.example.com/reports\"\n    })\n\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.CronJobs.run_now(client, job[\"id\"])\n    {:ok, history} = Miosa.CronJobs.list_executions(client, job[\"id\"])","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.create/2","doc":"Create a cron job.\n\nRequired: `:name`, `:schedule` (cron expression e.g. `\"0 4 * * *\"`).\nOptional: `:url`, `:payload`, `:timezone`, `:enabled`, `:idempotency_key`.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.delete/2","doc":"Delete a cron job by ID.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.get/2","doc":"Fetch a cron job by ID.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.get_execution/3","doc":"Get a specific execution record for a cron job.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#get_execution/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.list/2","doc":"List cron jobs for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.list_executions/3","doc":"List execution history for a cron job.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#list_executions/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.pause/2","doc":"Pause a cron job (stops future scheduled runs).","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#pause/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.resume/2","doc":"Resume a paused cron job.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#resume/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.run_now/2","doc":"Trigger an immediate execution of a cron job outside its schedule.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#run_now/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CronJobs.update/3","doc":"Update a cron job.\n\nPass any fields to update; nil values are dropped.","ref":"Miosa.CronJobs.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Dashboard","doc":"Dashboard — aggregated platform overview, polled on login.","ref":"Miosa.Dashboard.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Dashboard","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, summary} = Miosa.Dashboard.summary(client)","ref":"Miosa.Dashboard.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Dashboard.overview/1","doc":"Get the platform status and health overview (public endpoint).","ref":"Miosa.Dashboard.html#overview/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Dashboard.summary/1","doc":"Get the aggregated user dashboard payload.","ref":"Miosa.Dashboard.html#summary/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Databases","doc":"Managed Postgres databases — CRUD, lifecycle, credentials, logs.\n\nAll mutating calls send an `Idempotency-Key` header automatically.\nSupply `:idempotency_key` in `attrs` to use your own.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Databases","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, db} = Miosa.Databases.create(client, %{name: \"my-db\", plan: \"starter\"})\n    {:ok, creds} = Miosa.Databases.credentials(client, db[\"id\"])\n    IO.puts(creds[\"url\"])","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.create/2","doc":"Create a database.\n\nRequired: `:name`. Optional: `:plan`, `:region`, and any other attrs accepted\nby the API. Pass `:idempotency_key` to supply your own key.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.credentials/2","doc":"Get connection credentials (URL, host, port, user, password) for a database.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#credentials/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.delete/2","doc":"Delete a database by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.get/2","doc":"Fetch a database by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.list/2","doc":"List databases for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.logs/3","doc":"Get recent logs for a database.\n\nOptions:\n  * `:lines` — Number of log lines to return.\n  * `:since` — ISO 8601 timestamp to fetch logs since.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#logs/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.restart/2","doc":"Restart a database.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#restart/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.start/2","doc":"Start a stopped database.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#start/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Databases.stop/2","doc":"Stop a running database.","ref":"Miosa.Databases.html#stop/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Deployments","doc":"Deployments — sandbox → production publishing surface.\n\nBackend phase status (2026-05-15):\n  * `list/2`, `get/2`, `list_builds/2`, `get_build/3`, env helpers: pre-existing\n    repo flow.\n  * `publish/3`, `versions.*`, `rollback/3`, `domains.*`: Phase 2B/3 target —\n    returns the steady-state shape once the publish pipeline lands.\n  * `publish_from_sandbox/3`: backward-compatible bridge, works today.\n\nAll mutating calls send an `Idempotency-Key` header. Provide your own via\nthe `:idempotency_key` option or one is generated automatically.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Deployments","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, sandbox} = Miosa.Sandboxes.create(client, %{\n      name: \"smile-dental\",\n      external_workspace_id: \"dental-office-123\",\n      external_user_id: \"dr-smith-456\"\n    })\n\n    # ... agent writes files, runs dev server ...\n\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.Deployments.publish_from_sandbox(client, sandbox.id, %{\n      kind: \"static\",\n      environment: \"production\",\n      external_workspace_id: \"dental-office-123\"\n    })","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.add_domain/3","doc":"Attach a custom domain to a deployment. Returns DNS instructions.\n\nRequired: `:domain`. Optional: `:redirect_policy`, attribution,\n`:idempotency_key`.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#add_domain/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.create/2","doc":"Create a deployment.\n\nAccepts the documented Phase 2B/3 fields:\n\n  * `:name` (required)\n  * `:project_id` — if set, posts to `/projects/:id/deployments`\n  * `:source_type`, `:repo_url`, `:branch`\n  * `:build_command`, `:run_command`, `:auto_deploy`, `:metadata`\n  * `:external_workspace_id`, `:external_user_id`, `:external_project_id`\n  * `:idempotency_key`","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.delete/2","doc":"Delete a deployment.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.delete_domain/3","doc":"Detach a custom domain.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#delete_domain/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.get/2","doc":"Fetch a deployment by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.get_build/3","doc":"Get a specific build.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#get_build/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.get_version/3","doc":"Get a specific version.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#get_version/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.list/2","doc":"List deployments for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts filters:\n\n  * `:project_id`, `:state`, `:limit`, `:cursor`\n  * `:external_workspace_id`, `:external_user_id`, `:external_project_id`","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.list_builds/2","doc":"List builds for a deployment (legacy repo flow).","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#list_builds/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.list_domains/3","doc":"List custom domains attached to a deployment.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#list_domains/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.list_env/2","doc":"List env vars for a deployment.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#list_env/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.list_versions/3","doc":"List versions for a deployment. Same attribution filters as `list/2`.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#list_versions/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.promote_version/4","doc":"Promote a specific version to active. Optional `:environment`.\n\nDifferent from `publish/3`: promote points an existing ready version at\nthe active slot, no rebuild.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#promote_version/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.publish/3","doc":"Publish a sandbox to a deployment. Phase 2B/3 endpoint.\n\nRequired: `:source_sandbox_id`. Optional fields mirror the API contract\n(`:kind`, `:environment`, `:output_path`, `:build_command`, `:run_command`,\n`:port`, `:health_check_path`, `:data_services`, attribution).","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#publish/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.publish_from_sandbox/3","doc":"Publish through the backward-compatible bridge `/sandboxes/:id/deploy`.\nWorks today. Prefer `publish/3` once the release pipeline lands.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#publish_from_sandbox/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.rollback/3","doc":"Roll back a deployment to an older ready version.\n\nIf `:version_id` is omitted, the server defaults to the immediately\nprevious version.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#rollback/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.set_env/4","doc":"Set env vars on a deployment.\n\nPass `vars` as a map. Optional `:environment` selects which environment.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#set_env/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.update/3","doc":"Patch a deployment.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#update/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Deployments.verify_domain/3","doc":"Trigger DNS + TLS verification on a pending domain.","ref":"Miosa.Deployments.html#verify_domain/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Email","doc":"Admin email surface with sub-modules for campaigns, templates, and inbox.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/admin/email-{campaigns,templates,inbox}/`\nand require an admin credential (`msk_a_*` / `msk_p_*` or admin JWT).","ref":"Miosa.Email.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Sub-modules - Miosa.Email","doc":"* `Miosa.Email.Campaigns` — Bulk email send-out lifecycle\n  * `Miosa.Email.Templates` — Reusable templates keyed by name\n  * `Miosa.Email.Inbox` — Inbound and outbound direct messages","ref":"Miosa.Email.html#module-sub-modules"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns","doc":"Admin email campaign lifecycle (GET/POST/etc. `/admin/email-campaigns`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.cancel/2","doc":"Cancel a campaign (POST `/admin/email-campaigns/:campaign_id/cancel`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.html#cancel/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.create/2","doc":"Create an email campaign (POST `/admin/email-campaigns`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.deliveries/3","doc":"List per-recipient delivery records (GET `/admin/email-campaigns/:campaign_id/deliveries`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.html#deliveries/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.list/2","doc":"List email campaigns (GET `/admin/email-campaigns`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.recipient_count/2","doc":"Get estimated recipient count (GET `/admin/email-campaigns/recipient-count`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.html#recipient_count/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.send/3","doc":"Trigger send for a campaign (POST `/admin/email-campaigns/:campaign_id/send`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Campaigns.html#send/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Email.Inbox","doc":"Inbound and outbound direct messages (`/admin/email-inbox`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.archive/2","doc":"Archive a message (POST `/admin/email-inbox/:message_id/archive`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.html#archive/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.list/2","doc":"List inbox messages (GET `/admin/email-inbox`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.mark_read/2","doc":"Mark a message as read (POST `/admin/email-inbox/:message_id/read`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.html#mark_read/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.send/2","doc":"Send a direct message (POST `/admin/email-inbox/send`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Inbox.html#send/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Email.Templates","doc":"Reusable email templates keyed by name (`/admin/email-templates`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Templates.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Templates.create/3","doc":"Create an email template (POST `/admin/email-templates`).\n\n`key` is required — it uniquely identifies the template.","ref":"Miosa.Email.Templates.html#create/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Templates.list/2","doc":"List email templates (GET `/admin/email-templates`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Templates.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Templates.reset/2","doc":"Reset an email template to platform default (POST `/admin/email-templates/:key/reset`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Templates.html#reset/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Email.Templates.update/3","doc":"Update an email template (PUT `/admin/email-templates/:key`).","ref":"Miosa.Email.Templates.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Embeddings","doc":"OpenAI-compatible embedding vectors.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/intelligence/embeddings` and require an\n`mki_*` intelligence key.","ref":"Miosa.Embeddings.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Embeddings.create/4","doc":"Create one or more embedding vectors (POST `/intelligence/embeddings`).\n\n`input` may be a string or list of strings.\n\nReturns the full OpenAI-envelope response `%{\"object\" => \"list\", \"data\" => [...]}`.","ref":"Miosa.Embeddings.html#create/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.ExternalKeys","doc":"External BYOK keys — Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Groq, and similar.\n\nKeys are stored encrypted per-user and consumed by dashboard features\n(Builder, Optimal, etc.). The backend indexes external keys by `provider`,\nnot by a surrogate ID.","ref":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.ExternalKeys","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.ExternalKeys.create(client, \"anthropic\", \"sk-ant-...\")\n    {:ok, keys} = Miosa.ExternalKeys.list(client)","ref":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.create/4","doc":"Register an external provider key.\n\n`provider` — e.g. `\"anthropic\"`, `\"openai\"`, `\"google\"`, `\"groq\"`.\n`key` — the raw secret key string.\n`attrs` — optional additional fields accepted by the API.","ref":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.html#create/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.delete/2","doc":"Delete the stored key for a provider.","ref":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.list/1","doc":"List all configured external provider keys.","ref":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.resolve/2","doc":"Resolve (preview) the stored key for a provider.","ref":"Miosa.ExternalKeys.html#resolve/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains","doc":"Tenant-scoped custom domain management across all computers and deployments.\n\nThis is the flat listing at `/custom-domains`. Per-deployment domain\nmanagement lives in `Miosa.Deployments` (e.g. `add_domain/3`, `list_domains/2`).","ref":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.FlatCustomDomains","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, domain} = Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.create(client, %{\n      domain: \"app.example.com\",\n      target_id: \"depl_abc123\",\n      target_type: \"deployment\"\n    })\n\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.list(client)","ref":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.create/2","doc":"Attach a custom domain.\n\nRequired: `:domain`. Optional: `:target_id`, `:target_type`, `:redirect_policy`,\nattribution fields, `:idempotency_key`.","ref":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.delete/2","doc":"Delete a custom domain by ID.","ref":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.list/2","doc":"List all custom domains for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`,\n`:target_type`).","ref":"Miosa.FlatCustomDomains.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Functions","doc":"Edge functions — serverless, request-driven code that runs close to the user.\n\nFunctions support full CRUD and can be invoked synchronously.\nMutating calls send an `Idempotency-Key` header automatically.","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Functions","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, fn_} = Miosa.Functions.create(client, %{\n      name: \"resize-image\",\n      runtime: \"node18\",\n      source: \"export default (req) => new Response('ok')\"\n    })\n\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.Functions.invoke(client, fn_[\"id\"], %{\n      payload: %{url: \"https://example.com/logo.png\"}\n    })","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Functions.create/2","doc":"Create a function.\n\nRequired: `:name`. Optional: `:runtime`, `:source`, `:env`, `:metadata`,\n`:idempotency_key`.","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Functions.delete/2","doc":"Delete a function by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Functions.get/2","doc":"Fetch a function by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Functions.invoke/3","doc":"Invoke a function synchronously.\n\nOptional `opts`:\n  * `:payload` — Map to send as the request body.\n  * `:idempotency_key` — Idempotency key for the invocation.","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html#invoke/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Functions.list/2","doc":"List functions for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Functions.update/3","doc":"Update a function.\n\nPass any fields to update; nil values are dropped.","ref":"Miosa.Functions.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.HealthChecks","doc":"Health checks — uptime monitoring for URLs and TCP endpoints.\n\nMutating calls (create, update) send an `Idempotency-Key` header automatically.","ref":"Miosa.HealthChecks.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.HealthChecks","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, check} = Miosa.HealthChecks.create(client, %{\n      name: \"API health\",\n      url: \"https://api.example.com/health\",\n      interval_seconds: 60\n    })\n\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.HealthChecks.get(client, check[\"id\"])","ref":"Miosa.HealthChecks.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.HealthChecks.create/2","doc":"Create a health check.\n\nRequired: `:name`, `:url`. Optional: `:interval_seconds`, `:timeout_seconds`,\n`:expected_status`, `:method`, `:headers`, `:idempotency_key`.","ref":"Miosa.HealthChecks.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.HealthChecks.delete/2","doc":"Delete a health check by ID.","ref":"Miosa.HealthChecks.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.HealthChecks.get/2","doc":"Fetch a health check by ID.","ref":"Miosa.HealthChecks.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.HealthChecks.list/2","doc":"List health checks for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.HealthChecks.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.HealthChecks.update/3","doc":"Update a health check.\n\nPass any fields to update; nil values are dropped.","ref":"Miosa.HealthChecks.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Integrations","doc":"OAuth account-level integrations — GitHub, Slack, Linear, Discord.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Integrations","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, integrations} = Miosa.Integrations.list(client)\n    {:ok, %{\"url\" => url}} = Miosa.Integrations.start(client, \"github\")","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.catalog/1","doc":"List available providers in the integration catalog.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#catalog/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.disconnect/2","doc":"Disconnect (revoke) an integration by provider name.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#disconnect/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.discord_send_test/2","doc":"Send a test message to the connected Discord channel.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#discord_send_test/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.github_repos/1","doc":"List GitHub repositories accessible to this integration.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#github_repos/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.github_ssh_keys/1","doc":"List configured GitHub deploy (SSH) keys.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#github_ssh_keys/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.linear_create_issue/2","doc":"Create a Linear issue via the connected workspace.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#linear_create_issue/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.linear_start/1","doc":"Begin the Linear OAuth flow.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#linear_start/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.list/1","doc":"List active OAuth integrations for the tenant.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.refresh/2","doc":"Force-refresh the access token for a connected provider.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#refresh/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.slack_send_test/2","doc":"Send a test message to the connected Slack channel.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#slack_send_test/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Integrations.start/2","doc":"Begin the OAuth flow for a provider — returns an authorize URL.","ref":"Miosa.Integrations.html#start/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Mcp","doc":"Model Context Protocol — JSON-RPC dispatch and streaming SSE channel.\n\nClients (Claude Code, Cursor, Gemini CLI, GitHub Copilot) point at\n`/api/v1/mcp` with a `msk_*` Bearer token and discover the MIOSA\ntool-belt via this endpoint.","ref":"Miosa.Mcp.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Mcp","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.Mcp.dispatch(client, %{\n      method: \"tools/call\",\n      params: %{name: \"computer_screenshot\", arguments: %{computer_id: \"abc\"}}\n    })","ref":"Miosa.Mcp.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Mcp.close/1","doc":"Close (terminate) the MCP session.","ref":"Miosa.Mcp.html#close/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Mcp.dispatch/2","doc":"Send a JSON-RPC request to the MCP endpoint.\n\n`body` map may contain `:method`, `:params`, and any additional JSON-RPC\nfields (`id`, `jsonrpc`, etc.).","ref":"Miosa.Mcp.html#dispatch/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Mcp.listen/1","doc":"Open the MCP listen channel (GET).\n\nFor true SSE streaming use `Miosa.Client.stream_sse/4` directly.\nThis function returns the initial response body for one-shot callers.","ref":"Miosa.Mcp.html#listen/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Models","doc":"List available LLM models routed through the MIOSA intelligence gateway.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/intelligence/` and require an `mki_*`\nintelligence key or a JWT (dashboard users).","ref":"Miosa.Models.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Models.get/2","doc":"Get a single model by id, filtering the list response client-side.\n\nReturns `{:ok, model}` or `{:ok, nil}` if not found.","ref":"Miosa.Models.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Models.list/2","doc":"List all models available to the calling tenant (OpenAI-compatible shape).\n\nAccepts optional filter params (e.g. `provider:`, `type:`).","ref":"Miosa.Models.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.ProjectAuth","doc":"Project Auth — built-in authentication for generated apps inside\nsandboxes and deployments.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.ProjectAuth","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, status} = Miosa.ProjectAuth.status(client)\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.ProjectAuth.enable(client, %{provider: \"email\"})","ref":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.disable/1","doc":"Disable project auth.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.html#disable/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.enable/2","doc":"Enable project auth.\n\nPass an optional config map (e.g. `%{provider: \"email\"}`).","ref":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.html#enable/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.status/1","doc":"Get the current project-auth status and configuration.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.html#status/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.update/2","doc":"Update project-auth configuration.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectAuth.html#update/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations","doc":"Per-project integrations — Stripe, Resend, Twilio, and similar third-party\nprovider keys injected as env vars into sandbox/deployment VMs at boot.\n\nCredentials are encrypted at rest.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.ProjectIntegrations","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, catalog} = Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.catalog(client)\n    {:ok, integration} = Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.create(client, %{\n      provider: \"stripe\",\n      secret_key: \"sk_live_...\"\n    })","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.catalog/1","doc":"List supported providers and their configuration schemas.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html#catalog/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.create/2","doc":"Create a project integration.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.delete/2","doc":"Delete a project integration by ID.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.get/2","doc":"Get a project integration by ID.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.list/2","doc":"List project integrations.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.update/3","doc":"Update a project integration by ID.","ref":"Miosa.ProjectIntegrations.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults","doc":"Admin LLM provider routing config.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/admin/provider-defaults` and per-tenant\noverrides under `/api/v1/admin/tenants/:id/provider-config`. Requires an\nadmin credential (`msk_a_*` / `msk_p_*` or admin JWT).","ref":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.get/2","doc":"Return the defaults entry for a single provider name, or `{:ok, %{}}` if not found.","ref":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.get_tenant/2","doc":"Get per-tenant provider config override (GET `/admin/tenants/:tenant_id/provider-config`).","ref":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.html#get_tenant/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.list/1","doc":"Get the current fleet-wide provider defaults (GET `/admin/provider-defaults`).","ref":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.reset_tenant/2","doc":"Delete per-tenant provider config override (DELETE `/admin/tenants/:tenant_id/provider-config`).","ref":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.html#reset_tenant/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.set_tenant/3","doc":"Set per-tenant provider config override (PUT `/admin/tenants/:tenant_id/provider-config`).","ref":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.html#set_tenant/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.update/2","doc":"Replace the fleet-wide defaults (PUT `/admin/provider-defaults`).","ref":"Miosa.ProviderDefaults.html#update/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Regions","doc":"Datacenter regions, compute sizes, pricing, and community templates — read-only catalog.","ref":"Miosa.Regions.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Regions","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, regions} = Miosa.Regions.list_regions(client)\n    {:ok, sizes} = Miosa.Regions.list_sizes(client)","ref":"Miosa.Regions.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Regions.get_template/2","doc":"Get a single community template by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Regions.html#get_template/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Regions.list_regions/1","doc":"List available datacenter regions.","ref":"Miosa.Regions.html#list_regions/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Regions.list_sizes/1","doc":"List available compute sizes.","ref":"Miosa.Regions.html#list_sizes/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Regions.list_templates/1","doc":"List community computer templates.","ref":"Miosa.Regions.html#list_templates/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Regions.pricing/1","doc":"Get static compute pricing data.","ref":"Miosa.Regions.html#pricing/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Env","doc":"Per-sandbox env-var reader (GET `/sandboxes/:id/env`).\n\nThe backend currently exposes a read-only listing. To set env vars,\npass `env:` at sandbox creation time or via the template build-spec.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Env.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Env.list/2","doc":"List env vars for a sandbox (GET `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/env`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Env.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Events","doc":"SSE event streams for a sandbox.\n\n  * `GET /sandboxes/:id/events`             — stream/3\n  * `GET /sandboxes/:id/files/watch?path=…` — watch_dir/4","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Events.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Events.stream/3","doc":"Stream live sandbox events via SSE (GET `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/events`).\n\n`callback` is called for each event map with keys `type` and `data`.\nReturns `:ok` when the stream closes or `{:error, reason}` on failure.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Events.html#stream/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Events.watch_dir/5","doc":"Watch a directory for filesystem changes via SSE\n(GET `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/files/watch?path=…`).\n\n`callback` is called for each event map with keys `type` and `data`.\nReturns `:ok` when the stream closes or `{:error, reason}` on failure.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Events.html#watch_dir/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Sandbox.Events.watch_dir/5","doc":"* `:recursive` — When `true`, watch the directory tree recursively. Defaults to `false`.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Events.html#watch_dir/5-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews","doc":"Preview URL management for a sandbox.\n\nWraps `/sandboxes/:id/previews/*` — list, create, get, delete,\nshare (mint token), and revoke share tokens.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.create/4","doc":"Create a new preview for a port (POST `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/previews`).\n\n`port` is required. Additional opts are merged into the body.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.html#create/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.delete/3","doc":"Delete a preview (DELETE `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/previews/:preview_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.get/3","doc":"Get a preview by ID (GET `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/previews/:preview_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.list/2","doc":"List preview records for a sandbox (GET `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/previews`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.revoke_share/3","doc":"Invalidate every share token for a preview\n(DELETE `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/previews/:preview_id/share`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.html#revoke_share/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.share/4","doc":"Mint a share token for a preview\n(POST `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/previews/:preview_id/share`).\n\n`expires_in_sec` defaults to `3600` (one hour).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Previews.html#share/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Tags","doc":"Tag replacement for a sandbox (PATCH `/sandboxes/:id/tags`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Tags.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Tags.set/3","doc":"Replace the full tag list for a sandbox\n(PATCH `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/tags`).\n\nThe entire tag list is replaced — not merged.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Tags.html#set/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal","doc":"PTY session control for a sandbox.\n\n  * `POST   /sandboxes/:id/terminal`                — create/2\n  * `DELETE /sandboxes/:id/terminal/:session_id`    — delete/3","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal.create/3","doc":"Open a new PTY session (POST `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/terminal`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal.html#create/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options map keys - Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal.create/3","doc":"* `\"cols\"` — Terminal column width.\n  * `\"rows\"` — Terminal row count.\n  * `\"shell\"` — Shell binary path.\n  * `\"cwd\"` — Working directory.\n  * `\"env\"` — Environment variables map.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal.html#create/3-options-map-keys"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal.delete/3","doc":"Delete a PTY session (DELETE `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/terminal/:session_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal.html#delete/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates","doc":"Sandbox template management — define reusable base images for sandboxes.\n\nTemplates are built from a `build_spec` (a declarative definition of the\nbase image). Use `build_spec_schema/1` to discover the schema, `validate/2`\nto check a spec before creating a template, and `create_build/2` to trigger\na build.\n\nMutating calls (create, create_build) send an `Idempotency-Key` header\nautomatically.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.SandboxTemplates","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, schema} = Miosa.SandboxTemplates.build_spec_schema(client)\n\n    {:ok, tmpl} = Miosa.SandboxTemplates.create(client, %{\n      name: \"node-20-base\",\n      build_spec: %{runtime: \"node\", version: \"20\", packages: [\"curl\"]}\n    })\n\n    {:ok, build} = Miosa.SandboxTemplates.create_build(client, tmpl[\"id\"], %{})","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.build_spec_schema/1","doc":"Get the JSON schema for sandbox build specs.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#build_spec_schema/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.create/2","doc":"Create a sandbox template.\n\nRequired: `:name`, `:build_spec` (map). Optional: `:description`, `:metadata`,\n`:idempotency_key`.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.create_build/3","doc":"Trigger a new build for a sandbox template.\n\nOptional `attrs` may include build-time overrides. Pass `:idempotency_key`\nto supply your own idempotency key.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#create_build/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.get/2","doc":"Fetch a sandbox template by ID.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.list/2","doc":"List sandbox templates for the authenticated tenant.\n\nOptions:\n  * `:include_aliases` — Include template alias names. Defaults to `false`.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.list_builds/2","doc":"List builds for a sandbox template.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#list_builds/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.validate/2","doc":"Validate a build spec without creating a template.\n\nReturns validation errors or `{:ok, result}` with the normalized spec.","ref":"Miosa.SandboxTemplates.html#validate/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Settings","doc":"Tenant settings — workspace config, branding, and BYOK provider keys.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Settings","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, settings} = Miosa.Settings.get(client)\n    {:ok, _updated} = Miosa.Settings.update(client, %{default_region: \"us-east\"})","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.available_models/1","doc":"List models available to this tenant.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#available_models/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.compute_pricing/1","doc":"Get tenant-scoped compute pricing.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#compute_pricing/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.delete_provider_key/2","doc":"Delete a BYOK provider key by provider name.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#delete_provider_key/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.get/1","doc":"Get the current tenant settings.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#get/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.get_branding/1","doc":"Get tenant branding (logo, colors, custom wordmark).","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#get_branding/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.gpu_pricing/1","doc":"Get tenant-scoped GPU pricing.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#gpu_pricing/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.list_provider_keys/1","doc":"List tenant-level BYOK provider keys (Anthropic, OpenAI, etc.).","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#list_provider_keys/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.regions/1","doc":"List regions enabled for this tenant.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#regions/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.update/2","doc":"Update tenant settings.\n\nPass any settable fields as a map.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.update_branding/2","doc":"Update tenant branding.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#update_branding/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Settings.upsert_provider_key/3","doc":"Create or update a BYOK provider key.\n\nRequired: `provider` (e.g. `\"anthropic\"`) and `attrs` map containing at\nminimum `%{key: \"sk-...\"}`.","ref":"Miosa.Settings.html#upsert_provider_key/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.SnapshotsStandalone","doc":"Fleet-wide snapshot index for admin callers.\n\nRoutes live under `/api/v1/admin/snapshots/` and require an admin\ncredential. Per-computer snapshots remain nested under the computer's\ncheckpoint resource. This module exposes the fleet-wide read-only index\nused by the platform admin dashboard.","ref":"Miosa.SnapshotsStandalone.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SnapshotsStandalone.get/2","doc":"Get a snapshot by ID (GET `/admin/snapshots/:snapshot_id`).","ref":"Miosa.SnapshotsStandalone.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.SnapshotsStandalone.list/2","doc":"List all snapshots fleet-wide (GET `/admin/snapshots`).\n\nAccepts optional filter params (e.g. `%{computer_id: \"...\"}`, `%{status: \"ready\"}`).","ref":"Miosa.SnapshotsStandalone.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Storage","doc":"Managed S3-compatible object storage — buckets, objects, presigned URLs.\n\nObject keys are URL-encoded before inclusion in path segments.\nMutating bucket operations send an `Idempotency-Key` header automatically.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Storage","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, bucket} = Miosa.Storage.create_bucket(client, %{name: \"assets\"})\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.Storage.presign(client, bucket[\"id\"], %{\n      key: \"uploads/logo.png\",\n      operation: \"put\",\n      expires_in_sec: 600\n    })\n    IO.puts(result[\"url\"])","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.create_bucket/2","doc":"Create a storage bucket.\n\nRequired: `:name`. Optional: `:region`, `:public`, and any other attrs.\nPass `:idempotency_key` in `attrs` to supply your own idempotency key.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#create_bucket/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.delete_bucket/2","doc":"Delete a bucket by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#delete_bucket/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.delete_object/3","doc":"Delete an object from a bucket. The key is URL-encoded automatically.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#delete_object/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.get_bucket/2","doc":"Fetch a bucket by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#get_bucket/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.get_object/3","doc":"Download the raw bytes of an object.\n\nThe key is URL-encoded before being placed in the path.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#get_object/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.list_buckets/1","doc":"List all storage buckets for the authenticated tenant.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#list_buckets/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.list_objects/3","doc":"List objects in a bucket.\n\nOptions:\n  * `:prefix` — Filter by key prefix.\n  * `:limit` — Max objects to return.\n  * `:cursor` — Pagination cursor.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#list_objects/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.presign/3","doc":"Mint a presigned URL for direct browser upload or download.\n\nRequired `attrs`:\n  * `:key` — Object key.\n\nOptional `attrs`:\n  * `:operation` — `\"get\"` (default) or `\"put\"`.\n  * `:expires_in_sec` — Expiry in seconds. Defaults to `300`.\n  * `:content_type` — Required for `\"put\"` uploads.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#presign/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Storage.put_object/5","doc":"Upload bytes to an object key in a bucket.\n\n`content_type` defaults to `\"application/octet-stream\"`.\nThe key is URL-encoded before being placed in the path.","ref":"Miosa.Storage.html#put_object/5"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Tenant","doc":"Current tenant info — plan limits and live usage counters.","ref":"Miosa.Tenant.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Tenant","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, plan} = Miosa.Tenant.current(client)\n    IO.inspect(plan[\"plan\"])","ref":"Miosa.Tenant.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Tenant.current/1","doc":"Get the current tenant's plan, limits, and live usage counters.","ref":"Miosa.Tenant.html#current/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent","doc":"A server-sent event from a running agent session.","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent.event_type/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent.html#t:event_type/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent.from_sse/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentEvent.html#from_sse/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession","doc":"A CUA (Computer-Use Agent) session running on a computer.","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.AgentSession.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.Computer","doc":"Represents a MIOSA computer (VM workspace).","ref":"Miosa.Types.Computer.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Computer.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Computer.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Computer.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Computer.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.Computer.from_map/1","doc":"Builds a `Computer` struct from a raw API response map.","ref":"Miosa.Types.Computer.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent","doc":"A real-time lifecycle event emitted by a MIOSA computer.","ref":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent.event_type/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent.html#t:event_type/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent.from_sse/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent.html#from_sse/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.CreditBalance","doc":"Current credit balance for the authenticated tenant.","ref":"Miosa.Types.CreditBalance.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.CreditBalance.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CreditBalance.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.CreditBalance.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CreditBalance.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.CreditTransaction","doc":"A single credit debit or credit event.","ref":"Miosa.Types.CreditTransaction.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.CreditTransaction.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CreditTransaction.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.CreditTransaction.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CreditTransaction.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.CursorPosition","doc":"Current mouse cursor position on the desktop.","ref":"Miosa.Types.CursorPosition.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.CursorPosition.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CursorPosition.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.CursorPosition.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CursorPosition.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain","doc":"Represents a custom domain registered for a MIOSA computer.","ref":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.CustomDomain.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.DirEntry","doc":"A single entry returned by a directory listing.","ref":"Miosa.Types.DirEntry.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.DirEntry.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.DirEntry.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.DirEntry.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.DirEntry.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.ExecResult","doc":"Result of a command executed inside a computer.","ref":"Miosa.Types.ExecResult.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.ExecResult.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ExecResult.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.ExecResult.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ExecResult.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.ExportResult","doc":"Result of a file export operation.","ref":"Miosa.Types.ExportResult.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.ExportResult.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ExportResult.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.ExportResult.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ExportResult.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry","doc":"A file or directory entry in a computer's filesystem.","ref":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry.file_type/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry.html#t:file_type/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.FileEntry.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.FileStat","doc":"Detailed stat information for a single filesystem path.","ref":"Miosa.Types.FileStat.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.FileStat.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.FileStat.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.FileStat.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.FileStat.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicy","doc":"The full network policy for a computer, expressed as an ordered list of rules.","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicy.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicy.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicy.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicy.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicy.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule","doc":"A single network firewall rule (allow or deny).","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.action/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.html#t:action/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.direction/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.html#t:direction/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.NetworkPolicyRule.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.Service","doc":"Represents a managed background service running inside a computer.","ref":"Miosa.Types.Service.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Service.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Service.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Service.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Service.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.Service.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Service.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent","doc":"A single log line emitted by a background service.","ref":"Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot","doc":"Represents a disk checkpoint (snapshot) of a MIOSA computer.","ref":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Snapshot.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.Window","doc":"Represents an open window on the computer desktop.","ref":"Miosa.Types.Window.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Window.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Window.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.Window.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Window.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types.Workspace","doc":"Represents a MIOSA workspace — a named group of computers.","ref":"Miosa.Types.Workspace.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.Workspace.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Workspace.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Types.Workspace.from_map/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Types.Workspace.html#from_map/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Usage","doc":"Usage — current period summary, per-session metering, and report queries.","ref":"Miosa.Usage.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Usage","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, summary} = Miosa.Usage.current(client)\n    {:ok, sessions} = Miosa.Usage.sessions(client, %{limit: 100})","ref":"Miosa.Usage.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Usage.current/1","doc":"Get the current period usage summary.","ref":"Miosa.Usage.html#current/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Usage.report/2","doc":"Get a usage report for a period.\n\nOptions: `:period_start` and `:period_end` (ISO 8601 strings), plus any\nadditional filters accepted by the API.","ref":"Miosa.Usage.html#report/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Usage.sessions/2","doc":"List per-session metering events.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`,\n`:computer_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Usage.html#sessions/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Volumes","doc":"Persistent block storage volumes that survive instance restarts.\n\nVolumes can be attached to computers to provide durable storage\nbeyond the ephemeral rootfs.","ref":"Miosa.Volumes.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Volumes","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, vol} = Miosa.Volumes.create(client, %{name: \"data\", size_gb: 20})\n    {:ok, vol} = Miosa.Volumes.get(client, vol[\"id\"])","ref":"Miosa.Volumes.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Volumes.create/2","doc":"Create a volume.\n\nRequired: `:name`, `:size_gb`. Optional: `:region`, and any other attrs.\nPass `:idempotency_key` to supply your own idempotency key.","ref":"Miosa.Volumes.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Volumes.delete/2","doc":"Delete a volume by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Volumes.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Volumes.get/2","doc":"Fetch a volume by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Volumes.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Volumes.list/2","doc":"List volumes for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.Volumes.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Webhooks","doc":"Tenant-level outgoing webhooks — CRUD, test delivery, and delivery history.\n\nMutating calls (create, update, test) send an `Idempotency-Key` header\nautomatically.","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Webhooks","doc":"client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n\n    {:ok, wh} = Miosa.Webhooks.create(client, %{\n      url: \"https://api.example.com/hooks/miosa\",\n      events: [\"computer.started\", \"computer.stopped\"],\n      secret: \"whsec_...\"\n    })\n\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.Webhooks.test(client, wh[\"id\"])\n    {:ok, deliveries} = Miosa.Webhooks.deliveries(client, wh[\"id\"])","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Webhooks.create/2","doc":"Create a webhook.\n\nRequired: `:url`, `:events` (list of event type strings).\nOptional: `:secret`, `:enabled`, `:metadata`, `:idempotency_key`.","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Webhooks.delete/2","doc":"Delete a webhook by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Webhooks.deliveries/3","doc":"List recent delivery attempts for a webhook.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#deliveries/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Webhooks.get/2","doc":"Fetch a webhook by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Webhooks.list/2","doc":"List webhooks for the authenticated tenant.\n\nAccepts optional filters as a keyword list or map (e.g. `:limit`, `:cursor`).","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Webhooks.test/2","doc":"Send a test event to verify the webhook endpoint is reachable.","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#test/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Webhooks.update/3","doc":"Update a webhook.\n\nPass any fields to update; nil values are dropped.","ref":"Miosa.Webhooks.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa","doc":"Official Elixir SDK for the MIOSA API.\n\nMIOSA provides cloud computers (Linux VMs with a full desktop) accessible via\nAPI. This SDK covers computer management, desktop control, file operations,\nand command execution. The desktop and exec primitives let your own AI\nagent (Claude, GPT, your own model, etc.) drive a MIOSA computer.","ref":"Miosa.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Installation - Miosa","doc":"Add to your `mix.exs`:\n\n    defp deps do\n      [\n        {:miosa, \"~> 0.1.0\"}\n      ]\n    end","ref":"Miosa.html#module-installation"},{"type":"module","title":"Quick Start - Miosa","doc":"# Build a client\n    client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_your_api_key\")\n\n    # Create and start a computer\n    {:ok, computer} = Miosa.Computers.create(client, %{name: \"my-workspace\"})\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.start(client, computer.id)\n    {:ok, computer} = Miosa.Computer.wait_until_running(client, computer.id)\n\n    # Control the desktop\n    {:ok, png} = Miosa.Desktop.screenshot(client, computer.id)\n    :ok = Miosa.Desktop.click(client, computer.id, 500, 300)\n    :ok = Miosa.Desktop.type(client, computer.id, \"Hello, world!\")\n    :ok = Miosa.Desktop.key(client, computer.id, \"Return\")\n\n    # Run commands\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.Exec.bash(client, computer.id, \"echo hello\")\n    IO.puts(result.output)\n\n    # Upload and download files\n    :ok = Miosa.Files.upload(client, computer.id, \"./local.txt\", \"/home/user/file.txt\")\n    {:ok, content} = Miosa.Files.download(client, computer.id, \"/home/user/file.txt\")\n\n    # Drive the desktop yourself with your own AI agent — the SDK gives\n    # you the primitives (screenshot/click/type/key), you provide the loop:\n    {:ok, png} = Miosa.Desktop.screenshot(client, computer.id)\n    # ... pass `png` to your LLM, get back actions, replay via Miosa.Desktop ...\n\n    # Clean up\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.stop(client, computer.id)\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.destroy(client, computer.id)","ref":"Miosa.html#module-quick-start"},{"type":"module","title":"API Key - Miosa","doc":"Get your API key from the MIOSA dashboard at https://app.miosa.ai/settings/api.\nKeys have the format `msk_u_...` (user), `msk_a_...` (admin), or `msk_p_...` (platform).\n\nSet via environment variable for safety:\n\n    client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))","ref":"Miosa.html#module-api-key"},{"type":"module","title":"Modules - Miosa","doc":"* `Miosa.Computers` — Create, list, get, delete computers\n  * `Miosa.Computer` — Start, stop, restart, destroy a computer; wait for state transitions\n  * `Miosa.Sandboxes` — Thin helper that creates lightweight code-exec computers (`miosa-sandbox` template)\n  * `Miosa.Deployments` — Publish from a sandbox to a stable production URL; versions, rollback, custom domains\n  * `Miosa.Desktop` — Screenshot, click, type, key, scroll, drag, windows, cursor\n  * `Miosa.Exec` — Run bash and Python inside a computer\n  * `Miosa.Files` — Upload, download, list, export, delete, write files\n  * `Miosa.Credits` — Query credit balance, transactions, usage\n  * `Miosa.Admin` — Admin surface (`/admin/*`): users, tenants, credits, keys, Optimal model management (requires `msk_a_` / `msk_p_` key or admin JWT)\n  * `Miosa.Databases` — Managed Postgres databases: CRUD, start/stop/restart, credentials, logs\n  * `Miosa.Storage` — S3-compatible object storage: buckets, objects, presigned URLs\n  * `Miosa.Volumes` — Persistent block storage volumes: CRUD\n  * `Miosa.FlatCustomDomains` — Tenant-scoped custom domains across all computers/deployments\n  * `Miosa.Functions` — Edge functions: CRUD + synchronous invocation\n  * `Miosa.CronJobs` — Scheduled jobs: CRUD, pause/resume, run-now, execution history\n  * `Miosa.HealthChecks` — Uptime monitors: CRUD\n  * `Miosa.Webhooks` — Outgoing webhooks: CRUD, test delivery, delivery history\n  * `Miosa.SandboxTemplates` — Sandbox base images: CRUD, build-spec schema, validate, builds\n  * `Miosa.ApiKeys` — Programmatic API key management: list, create, revoke\n  * `Miosa.Tenant` — Current tenant plan limits and live usage counters\n  * `Miosa.Regions` — Datacenter regions, compute sizes, pricing, community templates\n  * `Miosa.Settings` — Tenant workspace config, branding, BYOK provider keys\n  * `Miosa.Dashboard` — Aggregated platform overview and health status\n  * `Miosa.Analytics` — Admin-scoped overview and timeseries metrics\n  * `Miosa.AuditLog` — Admin-scoped event stream\n  * `Miosa.Usage` — Current period summary, per-session metering, report queries\n  * `Miosa.Channels` — Notification channels (Slack, Discord, email): CRUD + enable/disable\n  * `Miosa.Integrations` — OAuth account-level integrations: GitHub, Slack, Linear, Discord\n  * `Miosa.ProjectIntegrations` — Per-project provider keys injected as env vars into VMs\n  * `Miosa.ProjectAuth` — Built-in auth for generated apps inside sandboxes/deployments\n  * `Miosa.ExternalKeys` — BYOK encrypted per-user provider keys (Anthropic, OpenAI, etc.)\n  * `Miosa.Mcp` — Model Context Protocol JSON-RPC dispatch and SSE channel\n  * `Miosa.Models` — List available LLM models via the intelligence gateway\n  * `Miosa.Completions` — OpenAI-compatible text and chat completions (streaming supported)\n  * `Miosa.Embeddings` — OpenAI-compatible embedding vectors\n  * `Miosa.ProviderDefaults` — Admin: fleet-wide LLM provider routing defaults + per-tenant overrides\n  * `Miosa.Benchmarks` — Admin: trigger and inspect platform benchmark runs\n  * `Miosa.CommandCenter` — Read-only views of the Optimal AI agent fleet + SSE event stream\n  * `Miosa.Community` — Community template and agent catalog with install + rate actions\n  * `Miosa.Email` — Admin email surface (sub-modules: `Miosa.Email.Campaigns`, `Miosa.Email.Templates`, `Miosa.Email.Inbox`)\n  * `Miosa.BuilderSessions` — Durable cross-device Builder UI session metadata\n  * `Miosa.SnapshotsStandalone` — Admin: fleet-wide snapshot index\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Terminal` — PTY session create and resize\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Osa` — In-VM OSA agent task dispatch, status, configure\n  * `Miosa.Computer.AutoStop` — Idle-timeout config read/update\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Inbox` — Per-computer inbound-email inbox config\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Env` — Encrypted env-var CRUD (list, set, update, delete, bulk_set)\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Logs` — Log snapshot + SSE stream\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Metrics` — Time-series RAM/CPU/credit metrics\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Ports` — Per-port visibility CRUD\n  * `Miosa.Computer.Volumes` — Volume attachment management\n  * `Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal` — Sandbox PTY session create and delete\n  * `Miosa.Sandbox.Events` — Sandbox SSE event stream\n  * `Miosa.Sandbox.Previews` — Preview URL CRUD + share/revoke token\n  * `Miosa.Sandbox.Env` — Per-sandbox env-var reader\n  * `Miosa.Sandbox.Tags` — Sandbox tag replacement\n  * `Miosa.Client` — Low-level HTTP client (use directly for custom requests)\n  * `Miosa.Types` — All response struct types\n  * `Miosa.Error` — Exception type raised/returned on errors","ref":"Miosa.html#module-modules"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.client/2","doc":"Creates a new MIOSA API client.\n\nThis is the entry point for all SDK operations. The returned client is a\nplain struct — it is stateless and safe to share across processes.","ref":"Miosa.html#client/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Arguments - Miosa.client/2","doc":"* `api_key` — Your MIOSA API key. Must start with `\"msk_\"`.","ref":"Miosa.html#client/2-arguments"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.client/2","doc":"* `:base_url` — Override the API base URL. Defaults to `https://api.miosa.ai/api/v1`.\n    Useful for local development with a self-hosted MIOSA instance.\n  * `:timeout` — Connection timeout in milliseconds. Defaults to `30_000`.\n  * `:receive_timeout` — Receive timeout for long-running requests. Defaults to `60_000`.\n  * `:retry` — Enable automatic retry on transient failures. Defaults to `false`.","ref":"Miosa.html#client/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Raises - Miosa.client/2","doc":"* `ArgumentError` — if the API key does not start with `\"msk_\"`.","ref":"Miosa.html#client/2-raises"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Miosa.client/2","doc":"client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_abcdef123\")\n\n    # Custom base URL for local dev\n    client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_abcdef123\", base_url: \"http://localhost:4000/api/v1\")","ref":"Miosa.html#client/2-example"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Client","doc":"HTTP transport layer for the MIOSA API.\n\nHolds configuration and wraps `Req` for all request types: JSON API calls,\nmultipart file uploads, binary downloads, and SSE streaming.\n\nConstruct a client via `Miosa.client/2` rather than using this module directly.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Options - Miosa.Client","doc":"* `:api_key` — Required. API key starting with `msk_`.\n  * `:base_url` — Override the API base URL. Defaults to `https://api.miosa.ai/api/v1`.\n  * `:timeout` — Request timeout in milliseconds. Defaults to `30_000`.\n  * `:receive_timeout` — Receive timeout for long-running requests. Defaults to `60_000`.\n  * `:retry` — Whether to retry failed requests. Defaults to `false`.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#module-options"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Client.result/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#t:result/1"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Client.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.delete/3","doc":"Performs a DELETE request and decodes the JSON response.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.get/3","doc":"Performs a GET request and decodes the JSON response.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.get_binary/3","doc":"Performs a GET request and returns the raw binary response body.\n\nUsed for downloading files and screenshots.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#get_binary/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.new/2","doc":"Builds a new `Miosa.Client` struct.\n\nValidates the API key format and constructs a base `Req` request with\ndefault headers and options pre-applied.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#new/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.patch/4","doc":"Performs a PATCH request with a JSON body and decodes the response.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#patch/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.post/4","doc":"Performs a POST request with a JSON body and decodes the response.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#post/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.post_multipart/4","doc":"Performs a multipart POST for file uploads.\n\n`parts` should be a list of `{name, value}` tuples or `{name, value, opts}` tuples\ncompatible with `Req`'s `:form_multipart` option.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#post_multipart/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.put/4","doc":"Performs a PUT request with a JSON body and decodes the response.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#put/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Client.stream_sse/4","doc":"Opens an SSE stream and calls `callback` for each parsed event.\n\nThe callback receives `{event_type :: String.t(), data :: String.t()}` tuples.\nThe stream is consumed until the connection closes or the server sends `data: [DONE]`.\n\nReturns `:ok` when the stream completes or `{:error, reason}` on failure.","ref":"Miosa.Client.html#stream_sse/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Admin","doc":"Admin surface — `/api/v1/admin/*`.\n\nRequires an admin credential: a `msk_a_*` / `msk_p_*` API key or an admin\nJWT. Calls from a user-role credential return `{:error, %Miosa.Error{status: 403}}`.\n\nFor endpoints not covered by the typed helpers below, use `request/5`\nwhich accepts an arbitrary method + path.","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Admin","doc":"client = Miosa.client(\"msk_a_...\")\n\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.Admin.grant_credits(client, \"tenant-uuid\", 1000, \"goodwill\")\n    {:ok, users} = Miosa.Admin.list_users(client, limit: 50, status: \"active\")\n    {:ok, _} = Miosa.Admin.change_tenant_plan(client, \"tenant-uuid\", \"pro\")","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Admin.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.api_key_stats/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#api_key_stats/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.audit_log/2","doc":"Read the platform audit log.\n\nOptions: `:limit`, `:cursor`.","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#audit_log/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.ban_user/4","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#ban_user/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.billing_summary/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#billing_summary/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.bulk_revoke_api_keys/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#bulk_revoke_api_keys/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.bulk_user_action/4","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#bulk_user_action/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.change_tenant_plan/4","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#change_tenant_plan/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.change_user_role/3","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#change_user_role/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.create_api_key/2","doc":"Create an API key on behalf of a tenant/user.\n\nRequired options: `:name`, `:tenant_id`, `:user_id`.\nOptional: `:key_type` (default `\"user\"`), `:purpose` (default `\"api\"`),\n`:rate_limit_rpm`, `:expires_at`, `:allowed_ips`.","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#create_api_key/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.dashboard/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#dashboard/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.deduct_credits/4","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#deduct_credits/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.delete_computer/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#delete_computer/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.delete_tenant/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#delete_tenant/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.delete_user/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#delete_user/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.detailed_health/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#detailed_health/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.force_logout/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#force_logout/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.get_user/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#get_user/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.grant_credits/5","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#grant_credits/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.list_api_keys/2","doc":"List API keys across tenants.\n\nOptions: `:limit`, `:cursor`, `:tenant_id`, `:status` (`\"active\" | \"revoked\" | \"expired\"`).","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#list_api_keys/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.list_computers/2","doc":"List all computers across tenants.\n\nOptions: `:limit`, `:cursor`, `:status`, `:tenant_id`.","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#list_computers/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.list_optimal_models/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#list_optimal_models/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.list_tenants/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#list_tenants/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.list_users/2","doc":"List users.\n\nOptions: `:limit`, `:cursor`, `:q`, `:status` (`\"active\" | \"suspended\" | \"deleted\"`).","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#list_users/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.optimal_status/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#optimal_status/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.purge_stale_computers/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#purge_stale_computers/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.refund_credits/5","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#refund_credits/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.request/5","doc":"Call any admin endpoint directly.\n\n`method` is one of `:get`, `:post`, `:put`, `:patch`, `:delete`.\n`path` is relative to `/api/v1` and should include the `/admin` prefix.","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#request/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.restart_computer/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#restart_computer/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.resume_computer/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#resume_computer/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.revoke_api_key/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#revoke_api_key/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.stats/1","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#stats/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.suspend_computer/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#suspend_computer/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.suspend_tenant/3","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#suspend_tenant/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.suspend_user/3","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#suspend_user/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.switch_optimal_model/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#switch_optimal_model/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.tenant_balance/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#tenant_balance/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.tenant_credit_history/3","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#tenant_credit_history/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.tenant_detail/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#tenant_detail/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.unban_user/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#unban_user/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.unsuspend_tenant/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#unsuspend_tenant/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.unsuspend_user/2","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#unsuspend_user/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Admin.update_user/3","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Admin.html#update_user/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints","doc":"Create and restore disk snapshots (checkpoints) of MIOSA computers.\n\nA checkpoint captures the full disk state of a computer at a point in time.\nRestoring a checkpoint rolls the computer back to that exact state.","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Checkpoints","doc":"{:ok, snap} = Miosa.Checkpoints.create(client, computer_id, %{\n      name: \"before-deploy\"\n    })\n\n    {:ok, snaps} = Miosa.Checkpoints.list(client, computer_id)\n    {:ok, snap} = Miosa.Checkpoints.get(client, computer_id, snap.id)\n\n    # Restore with optional SSE progress streaming\n    :ok = Miosa.Checkpoints.restore(client, computer_id, snap.id)\n\n    # Stream restore progress events\n    events = Miosa.Checkpoints.restore_stream(client, computer_id, snap.id)\n    Enum.each(events, fn event -> IO.inspect(event) end)\n\n    :ok = Miosa.Checkpoints.delete(client, computer_id, snap.id)","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints.create_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#t:create_params/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints.create/3","doc":"Creates a new checkpoint (snapshot) of a computer's disk state.\n\nThe computer should be stopped or in a consistent state before snapshotting.","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#create/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Params - Miosa.Checkpoints.create/3","doc":"* `:name` — Optional display name.\n  * `:description` — Optional description of what this snapshot represents.","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#create/3-params"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints.delete/3","doc":"Deletes a checkpoint permanently.","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints.get/3","doc":"Fetches a single checkpoint by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints.list/2","doc":"Lists all checkpoints for a computer, ordered by creation time (newest first).","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints.restore/3","doc":"Restores a computer to a checkpoint state (fire-and-forget).\n\nThe API will stop the computer (if running), restore the disk, and restart it.\nReturns `:ok` once the restore request is accepted.\n\nUse `restore_stream/3` to receive incremental progress events via an Elixir\n`Stream`.","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#restore/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Checkpoints.restore_stream/3","doc":"Restores a checkpoint and returns a `Stream` of progress events.\n\nEach element yielded by the stream is a map with at least `:event` and\n`:data` keys. The stream ends when the restore completes or fails.","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#restore_stream/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Miosa.Checkpoints.restore_stream/3","doc":"stream = Miosa.Checkpoints.restore_stream(client, computer_id, snap_id)\n    Enum.each(stream, fn %{event: e, data: d} -> IO.puts(\"#{e}: #{inspect(d)}\") end)","ref":"Miosa.Checkpoints.html#restore_stream/3-example"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer","doc":"Lifecycle actions for a specific MIOSA computer.\n\nThis module covers power operations: start, stop, restart, and destroy.\nAll functions require a `Miosa.Client` and a computer ID string.\n\nFor creating and listing computers, see `Miosa.Computers`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Computer","doc":"client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_...\")\n\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.start(client, \"comp_abc123\")\n\n    # Poll until running\n    {:ok, computer} = Miosa.Computer.wait_until_running(client, \"comp_abc123\")\n\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.stop(client, \"comp_abc123\")\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.destroy(client, \"comp_abc123\")","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.apps/2","doc":"List installed applications on a computer (GET `/computers/:computer_id/apps`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#apps/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.clone/3","doc":"Clone a computer into a new computer (POST `/computers/:computer_id/clone`).\n\nOptional `attrs` are merged into the clone creation payload.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#clone/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.destroy/2","doc":"Destroys a computer permanently.\n\nThis is equivalent to `Miosa.Computers.delete/2` with `force: true`.\nAll data is lost. This action cannot be undone.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#destroy/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.move/3","doc":"Move a computer to a different region or host\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/move`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#move/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.preview_url/4","doc":"Returns the preview URL for a specific port on the computer.\n\nThe preview URL provides authenticated HTTP access to a service running inside\nthe computer. Append a path after the returned URL as needed.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#preview_url/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Miosa.Computer.preview_url/4","doc":"* `computer_id` — Computer ID string.\n  * `port` — Port number the service is listening on inside the VM.\n  * `opts`:\n    * `:base_url` — Override the base domain. Defaults to `\"https://preview.miosa.ai\"`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#preview_url/4-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Miosa.Computer.preview_url/4","doc":"url = Miosa.Computer.preview_url(client, \"comp_abc\", 3000)\n    # => \"https://preview.miosa.ai/comp_abc/3000\"","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#preview_url/4-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.public_url/3","doc":"Returns the public URL for the computer desktop stream.\n\nThis URL is the root access point for the computer's web interface\n(VNC/KasmVNC). Requires the computer to be running and `:visibility`\nset to `:public` or authenticated with an API key.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#public_url/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Miosa.Computer.public_url/3","doc":"url = Miosa.Computer.public_url(client, \"comp_abc\")\n    # => \"https://desktop.miosa.ai/comp_abc\"","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#public_url/3-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.resize/3","doc":"Resize a computer (PATCH `/computers/:computer_id/resize`).\n\nPass `cpu`, `memory_mb`, or any other size params.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#resize/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.restart/2","doc":"Restarts a running computer.\n\nEquivalent to stop + start. The computer will be unavailable briefly\nduring the restart.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#restart/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.screenshot_region/6","doc":"Take a screenshot of a sub-region\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/screenshot`).\n\nCoordinates are in 0–1000 space (MIOSA canonical coordinate system).\nReturns raw PNG binary.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#screenshot_region/6"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.start/2","doc":"Starts a stopped computer.\n\nReturns `:ok` once the start request is accepted. The computer transitions\nthrough `:starting` → `:running`. Use `wait_until_running/3` to block until\nready.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#start/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.stop/2","doc":"Stops a running computer (graceful shutdown).\n\nThe computer status transitions to `:stopping` → `:stopped`.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#stop/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.stream_token/2","doc":"Issue a short-lived stream token for a computer\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/stream-token`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#stream_token/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.urls/2","doc":"List the named public URLs for a computer (GET `/computers/:computer_id/urls`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#urls/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.vnc_credentials/2","doc":"Fetch the VNC/KasmVNC credentials for a computer\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/vnc-credentials`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#vnc_credentials/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.wait_until_running/3","doc":"Blocks until the computer reaches `:running` status or times out.\n\nPolls `Miosa.Computers.get/2` every 2 seconds.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#wait_until_running/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Computer.wait_until_running/3","doc":"* `:timeout` — Maximum wait time in milliseconds. Defaults to `300_000` (5 minutes).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#wait_until_running/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Miosa.Computer.wait_until_running/3","doc":"* `{:ok, computer}` — when the computer is running.\n  * `{:error, :timeout}` — if the computer did not reach `:running` within the timeout.\n  * `{:error, reason}` — if the computer reaches `:error` status or an API error occurs.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#wait_until_running/3-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.wait_until_stopped/3","doc":"Blocks until the computer reaches `:stopped` status or times out.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#wait_until_stopped/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Computer.wait_until_stopped/3","doc":"* `:timeout` — Maximum wait time in milliseconds. Defaults to `300_000` (5 minutes).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.html#wait_until_stopped/3-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computer.Agent","doc":"Computer-Use Agent (CUA) session management for a computer.\n\nWraps:\n  * `POST   /computers/:id/cua/sessions`          — run/4\n  * `GET    /computers/:id/cua/sessions`          — list/2\n  * `GET    /computers/:id/cua/sessions/:sid`     — get/3\n  * `DELETE /computers/:id/cua/sessions/:sid`     — cancel/3","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.cancel/3","doc":"Cancel a running CUA session\n(DELETE `/computers/:computer_id/cua/sessions/:session_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.html#cancel/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.get/3","doc":"Retrieve a single CUA session by ID\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/cua/sessions/:session_id`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.list/2","doc":"List all CUA sessions for a computer\n(GET `/computers/:computer_id/cua/sessions`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.run/4","doc":"Create and start a CUA session for a computer\n(POST `/computers/:computer_id/cua/sessions`).","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.html#run/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options map keys - Miosa.Computer.Agent.run/4","doc":"* `\"model\"` — Override the AI model (e.g. `\"claude-3-5-sonnet-latest\"`).\n  * `\"max_steps\"` — Maximum number of agent steps before stopping.\n  * `\"tools\"` — List of additional tool names to enable.\n  * `\"timeout\"` — Session timeout in seconds.","ref":"Miosa.Computer.Agent.html#run/4-options-map-keys"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Computers","doc":"Manage MIOSA computers (VM workspaces).\n\nComputers are the core resource: isolated Linux VMs with a full desktop\nenvironment, terminal access, and an OSA agent running inside each one.","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Computers","doc":"client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_...\")\n\n    {:ok, computer} = Miosa.Computers.create(client, %{\n      name: \"my-agent-workspace\",\n      template_type: \"miosa-desktop\",\n      size: \"small\"\n    })\n\n    {:ok, computers} = Miosa.Computers.list(client)\n    {:ok, computer} = Miosa.Computers.get(client, computer.id)\n    :ok = Miosa.Computers.delete(client, computer.id)","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Computers.create_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html#t:create_params/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computers.create/2","doc":"Creates a new computer.\n\nThe computer starts in `:creating` status. Use `Miosa.Computer.start/2` to\nboot it, or poll `get/2` until the status becomes `:running`.","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Params - Miosa.Computers.create/2","doc":"* `:name` — Display name (optional, auto-generated if omitted).\n  * `:template_type` — Template to use. Defaults to `\"miosa-desktop\"`.\n  * `:size` — VM size: `\"small\"` (default), `\"medium\"`, `\"large\"`.\n  * `:metadata` — Arbitrary key-value map stored with the computer.","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html#create/2-params"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computers.delete/3","doc":"Deletes a computer and destroys all associated resources.\n\nThe computer must be stopped before deletion, or pass `force: true` to\nforce destroy a running computer (data will be lost).","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computers.get/2","doc":"Fetches a single computer by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Computers.list/1","doc":"Lists all computers for the authenticated tenant.\n\nReturns a list of `Miosa.Types.Computer` structs ordered by creation time\n(newest first).","ref":"Miosa.Computers.html#list/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Credits","doc":"Query credit balance, transaction history, and usage for the authenticated tenant.\n\nCredits are consumed by compute time and AI agent calls. The balance is\nshared across all computers and sessions for your account.","ref":"Miosa.Credits.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Credits","doc":"{:ok, balance} = Miosa.Credits.balance(client)\n    IO.puts(\"Credits remaining: #{balance.balance}\")\n\n    {:ok, txns} = Miosa.Credits.transactions(client, limit: 20)\n    {:ok, usage} = Miosa.Credits.usage(client)","ref":"Miosa.Credits.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Credits.balance/1","doc":"Returns the current credit balance for the authenticated tenant.","ref":"Miosa.Credits.html#balance/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Credits.transactions/2","doc":"Lists credit transactions (debits and credits).","ref":"Miosa.Credits.html#transactions/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Credits.transactions/2","doc":"* `:limit` — Maximum number of transactions. Defaults to `50`.\n  * `:offset` — Pagination offset. Defaults to `0`.\n  * `:type` — Filter by type: `\"debit\"`, `\"credit\"`, `\"promo\"`.","ref":"Miosa.Credits.html#transactions/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Credits.usage/2","doc":"Returns aggregated usage statistics for the tenant.\n\nReturns a raw map as usage schema varies by plan and time period.","ref":"Miosa.Credits.html#usage/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.CustomDomains","doc":"Register and verify custom domains for MIOSA computers.\n\nCustom domains allow you to expose a service running inside a computer at\na user-friendly hostname (e.g. `app.example.com`) instead of the default\ngenerated URL.","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Workflow - Miosa.CustomDomains","doc":"1. `register/3` — claim the domain against a computer + port.\n2. Follow the DNS instructions returned in the `CustomDomain` struct.\n3. `verify/3` — trigger domain verification; status transitions to `:active`.\n4. `delete/3` — remove the domain when no longer needed.","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#module-workflow"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.CustomDomains","doc":"{:ok, domain} = Miosa.CustomDomains.register(client, computer_id, %{\n      domain: \"app.example.com\",\n      port: 3000\n    })\n\n    {:ok, domains} = Miosa.CustomDomains.list(client, computer_id)\n    {:ok, domain} = Miosa.CustomDomains.verify(client, computer_id, domain.id)\n    :ok = Miosa.CustomDomains.delete(client, computer_id, domain.id)","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.CustomDomains.register_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#t:register_params/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CustomDomains.delete/3","doc":"Removes a custom domain registration.\n\nIn-flight requests to the domain will immediately return 404 after deletion.","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CustomDomains.list/2","doc":"Lists all custom domains registered for a computer.","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CustomDomains.register/3","doc":"Registers a custom domain for a computer.","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#register/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Params - Miosa.CustomDomains.register/3","doc":"* `:domain` — Required. The fully-qualified domain name.\n  * `:port` — Port inside the computer to route traffic to. Defaults to `80`.\n  * `:tls` — Whether to provision TLS. Defaults to `true`.\n\nReturns a `CustomDomain` struct whose `:dns_instructions` field contains\nthe CNAME or A-record value to configure with your DNS provider.","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#register/3-params"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.CustomDomains.verify/3","doc":"Triggers domain ownership verification.\n\nThe API checks that the required DNS record is in place. On success the\ndomain transitions to `:active` status.\n\nReturns the updated `CustomDomain` struct.","ref":"Miosa.CustomDomains.html#verify/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Desktop","doc":"Control the desktop environment of a running MIOSA computer.\n\nAll actions interact with the live X11 desktop inside the VM via the\nMIOSA API. The computer must be in `:running` status.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Input Actions - Miosa.Desktop","doc":"- `screenshot/2` — Capture the current desktop as PNG bytes\n- `click/4` — Left-click at coordinates\n- `double_click/4` — Double-click at coordinates\n- `right_click/4` — Right-click at coordinates\n- `drag/6` — Click-drag from one point to another\n- `type/3` — Type a string of text\n- `key/3` — Press a keyboard shortcut (e.g. `\"ctrl+c\"`, `\"Return\"`)\n- `scroll/5` — Scroll the mouse wheel at coordinates\n- `wait/3` — Sleep inside the VM for N milliseconds","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#module-input-actions"},{"type":"module","title":"Window Management - Miosa.Desktop","doc":"- `windows/2` — List open windows\n- `cursor/2` — Get current cursor position\n- `focus_window/3` — Bring a window to the foreground by ID\n- `launch/3` — Launch an application by name","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#module-window-management"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Desktop","doc":"{:ok, png} = Miosa.Desktop.screenshot(client, computer_id)\n    File.write!(\"screen.png\", png)\n\n    :ok = Miosa.Desktop.click(client, computer_id, 500, 300)\n    :ok = Miosa.Desktop.type(client, computer_id, \"Hello, world!\")\n    :ok = Miosa.Desktop.key(client, computer_id, \"Return\")\n    :ok = Miosa.Desktop.key(client, computer_id, \"ctrl+c\")","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.click/4","doc":"Left-clicks at the given `(x, y)` desktop coordinates.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#click/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.cursor/2","doc":"Returns the current mouse cursor position on the desktop.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#cursor/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.double_click/4","doc":"Double-clicks at the given `(x, y)` desktop coordinates.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#double_click/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.drag/6","doc":"Click-drags from `(from_x, from_y)` to `(to_x, to_y)`.\n\nUseful for selecting text, resizing windows, or drag-and-drop operations.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#drag/6"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.focus_window/3","doc":"Brings a window to the foreground by its window ID.\n\nUse `windows/2` to list window IDs.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#focus_window/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.key/3","doc":"Presses a keyboard key or shortcut combination.\n\nUses X11 keysym notation. Common examples:\n- `\"Return\"` — Enter key\n- `\"Escape\"` — Escape key\n- `\"ctrl+c\"` — Copy\n- `\"ctrl+v\"` — Paste\n- `\"ctrl+a\"` — Select all\n- `\"alt+F4\"` — Close window\n- `\"super\"` — Windows/Super key\n- `\"Tab\"` — Tab key\n- `\"BackSpace\"` — Backspace","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#key/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.launch/3","doc":"Launches an application by name or command.\n\nExamples:\n- `\"firefox\"`\n- `\"code\"` (VS Code)\n- `\"xterm\"`\n- `\"nautilus /home/user\"`","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#launch/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.move/4","doc":"Moves the mouse cursor to `(x, y)` without clicking.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#move/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.right_click/4","doc":"Right-clicks at the given `(x, y)` desktop coordinates.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#right_click/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.screenshot/2","doc":"Captures a screenshot of the computer desktop.\n\nReturns raw PNG bytes. Save with `File.write!/2` or encode as base64\nwith `Base.encode64/1`.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#screenshot/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.scroll/6","doc":"Scrolls the mouse wheel at the given `(x, y)` coordinates.\n\n`direction` is `\"up\"` or `\"down\"`. `amount` is the number of scroll clicks\n(default `3`).","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#scroll/6"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.type/3","doc":"Types the given text string at the current cursor position.\n\nSpecial characters and Unicode are supported. For keyboard shortcuts\n(Ctrl, Alt, etc.), use `key/3` instead.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#type/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.wait/3","doc":"Waits (sleeps) for `ms` milliseconds inside the VM.\n\nUseful when scripting sequences that need a pause after an action\n(e.g. waiting for an animation or page load). Prefer agent sessions\nfor intelligent waiting.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#wait/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Desktop.windows/2","doc":"Lists all open windows on the desktop.\n\nReturns a list of `Miosa.Types.Window` structs with position and size.","ref":"Miosa.Desktop.html#windows/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Events","doc":"Subscribe to real-time computer lifecycle events via SSE.\n\n`subscribe/2` returns a `Stream` that yields `Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent`\nstructs as they arrive. The stream is lazy and pulls events from the SSE\nconnection on demand.\n\nChoosing a `Stream` over a GenServer fan-out is idiomatic for Elixir\nconsumers: callers can `Enum.take/2`, pipe into `Flow`, or simply\n`Stream.run/1` — all standard `Enumerable` operations apply. A GenServer\nis unnecessary unless the caller needs concurrent fan-out to multiple\nprocesses, which can be achieved by spawning a `Task` that runs the stream\nand uses `Process.send/2` to forward events — a pattern the caller controls\nwithout SDK coupling.","ref":"Miosa.Events.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Events","doc":"stream = Miosa.Events.subscribe(client, computer_id)\n\n    # Process events until the stream ends (server closes connection)\n    Enum.each(stream, fn event ->\n      IO.inspect(event)\n    end)\n\n    # Async: spawn a Task and receive events as messages\n    parent = self()\n    Task.start(fn ->\n      Miosa.Events.subscribe(client, computer_id)\n      |> Enum.each(fn event -> send(parent, {:computer_event, event}) end)\n    end)","ref":"Miosa.Events.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Events.subscribe_opts/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Events.html#t:subscribe_opts/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Events.subscribe/3","doc":"Returns a `Stream` of `Miosa.Types.ComputerEvent` structs for the given computer.\n\nThe stream connects to the server-sent events endpoint for the computer and\nyields events as they arrive. The stream ends when the SSE connection closes\n(server-side) or the caller stops consuming it.","ref":"Miosa.Events.html#subscribe/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Events.subscribe/3","doc":"* `:timeout` — Per-event receive timeout in milliseconds. Defaults to `300_000`.","ref":"Miosa.Events.html#subscribe/3-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Exec","doc":"Execute commands and scripts inside a running MIOSA computer.\n\nBoth Bash and Python execution are supported. Commands run with the default\nuser's environment inside the VM.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Exec","doc":"{:ok, result} = Miosa.Exec.bash(client, computer_id, \"ls -la /home/user\")\n    IO.puts(result.output)\n    IO.puts(\"Exit code: #{result.exit_code}\")\n\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.Exec.python(client, computer_id, \"\"\"\n      import json\n      data = {\"hello\": \"world\"}\n      print(json.dumps(data))\n    \"\"\")","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.bash/4","doc":"Executes a Bash command inside the computer.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#bash/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Exec.bash/4","doc":"* `:timeout` — Execution timeout in milliseconds. Defaults to `30_000`.\n  * `:working_dir` — Working directory for the command. Defaults to `\"/home/user\"`.\n  * `:env` — Map of additional environment variables.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#bash/4-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - Miosa.Exec.bash/4","doc":"`{:ok, result}` with an `ExecResult` containing `:output`, `:stdout`,\n`:stderr`, and `:exit_code`. On API error, returns `{:error, reason}`.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#bash/4-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.bash!/4","doc":"Convenience wrapper: runs bash and raises `Miosa.Error` on failure.\n\nReturns the `ExecResult` directly (not wrapped in `{:ok, _}`).","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#bash!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.python/4","doc":"Executes a Python script inside the computer.\n\nThe script runs with the system Python 3 interpreter. Common packages\n(requests, numpy, pandas, etc.) may be pre-installed depending on the\ncomputer template.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#python/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Exec.python/4","doc":"* `:timeout` — Execution timeout in milliseconds. Defaults to `30_000`.\n  * `:working_dir` — Working directory. Defaults to `\"/home/user\"`.\n  * `:env` — Map of additional environment variables.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#python/4-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.python!/4","doc":"Convenience wrapper: runs python and raises `Miosa.Error` on failure.\n\nReturns the `ExecResult` directly (not wrapped in `{:ok, _}`).","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#python!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.spawn/4","doc":"Spawns an interactive command session over WebSocket and returns a\n`Miosa.Exec.Command` GenServer PID.\n\nThe returned PID represents a live WebSocket connection to the computer.\nUse `Miosa.Exec.Command.send_stdin/2`, `close_stdin/1`, `resize/3`, and\n`await/2` to interact with the running process.\n\nThe GenServer owns the WebSocket connection and terminates it on shutdown.\nCallers should always call `Miosa.Exec.Command.await/2` to drain the session\nand ensure the underlying connection is cleaned up.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#spawn/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Exec.spawn/4","doc":"* `:pty` — Allocate a pseudo-terminal. Required for interactive programs\n    like shells. Defaults to `false`.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#spawn/4-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Miosa.Exec.spawn/4","doc":"{:ok, cmd} = Miosa.Exec.spawn(client, computer_id, \"bash\", pty: true)\n    :ok = Miosa.Exec.Command.send_stdin(cmd, \"echo hello\\n\")\n    :ok = Miosa.Exec.Command.send_stdin(cmd, \"exit\\n\")\n    {:ok, 0} = Miosa.Exec.Command.await(cmd, 5_000)","ref":"Miosa.Exec.html#spawn/4-example"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Exec.Command","doc":"A GenServer holding a long-lived interactive command session over WebSocket.\n\nObtained via `Miosa.Exec.spawn/3`. Provides stdin/stdout interaction and\nterminal resize for PTY-based commands.\n\nThe underlying WebSocket is managed via `:gun`. The GenServer owns the\nconnection and shuts it down on termination.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Exec.Command","doc":"{:ok, cmd} = Miosa.Exec.spawn(client, computer_id, \"bash\")\n\n    :ok = Miosa.Exec.Command.send_stdin(cmd, \"ls -la\\n\")\n    :ok = Miosa.Exec.Command.resize(cmd, 120, 40)\n\n    # Block until the command exits (or timeout)\n    {:ok, exit_code} = Miosa.Exec.Command.await(cmd, 30_000)","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Exec.Command.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.Command.await/2","doc":"Blocks until the command exits and returns `{:ok, exit_code}`.\n\nReturns `{:error, :timeout}` if the command does not exit within `timeout_ms`.\nThe GenServer process is stopped after `await/2` returns.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html#await/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.Command.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.Command.close_stdin/1","doc":"Signals stdin EOF to the command (closes the write half of the WebSocket).","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html#close_stdin/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.Command.resize/3","doc":"Sends a terminal resize event (SIGWINCH) to the running command.\n\nOnly meaningful for PTY-based commands (those started with `pty: true`).","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html#resize/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Exec.Command.send_stdin/2","doc":"Sends data to the command's stdin.\n\n`data` should be a binary string (may include newlines).\nReturns `:ok` immediately; delivery is async over the WebSocket.","ref":"Miosa.Exec.Command.html#send_stdin/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Files","doc":"Upload, download, list, and manage files inside a MIOSA computer.\n\nFile operations interact with the computer's filesystem via the MIOSA API.\nPaths are absolute paths inside the VM (e.g. `\"/home/user/myfile.txt\"`).","ref":"Miosa.Files.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Files","doc":"# Upload a local file\n    :ok = Miosa.Files.upload(client, computer_id, \"./local.txt\", \"/home/user/remote.txt\")\n\n    # Download a file\n    {:ok, content} = Miosa.Files.download(client, computer_id, \"/home/user/remote.txt\")\n    File.write!(\"local_copy.txt\", content)\n\n    # List directory contents\n    {:ok, entries} = Miosa.Files.list(client, computer_id, \"/home/user\")\n    Enum.each(entries, fn e -> IO.puts(\"#{e.type}: #{e.name}\") end)\n\n    # Get a temporary download URL\n    {:ok, export} = Miosa.Files.export(client, computer_id, \"/home/user/report.pdf\")\n    IO.puts(\"Download at: #{export.url}\")\n\n    # Delete a file\n    :ok = Miosa.Files.delete(client, computer_id, \"/home/user/old.txt\")","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Files.delete/4","doc":"Deletes a file or directory on the computer.","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#delete/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Files.delete/4","doc":"* `:recursive` — Delete directories recursively. Defaults to `false`.","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#delete/4-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Files.download/3","doc":"Downloads a file from the computer and returns its binary content.\n\nReturns `{:ok, binary()}` where `binary()` is the raw file bytes.","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#download/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Files.download_to/4","doc":"Downloads a file and writes it to a local path.\n\nReturns `:ok` on success or `{:error, reason}` on failure.\n`reason` may be a `Miosa.Error` (API failure) or `File.Error` (filesystem write failure).","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#download_to/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Files.export/3","doc":"Generates a temporary signed download URL for a file on the computer.\n\nThe URL is publicly accessible for a limited time (typically 15–60 minutes).\nUseful for sharing files without streaming through the API.\n\nReturns `{:ok, Miosa.Types.ExportResult.t()}` with `:url` and `:expires_at`.","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#export/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Files.list/3","doc":"Lists the contents of a directory on the computer.\n\nReturns a list of `Miosa.Types.FileEntry` structs, each with `:name`,\n`:path`, `:type` (`:file`, `:directory`, `:symlink`), `:size`, and `:modified_at`.","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#list/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Files.upload/5","doc":"Uploads a local file to the computer at the given remote path.\n\n`local_path` can be:\n- A filesystem path string (`\"./myfile.txt\"`)\n- A `{:binary, content, filename}` tuple for in-memory content","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#upload/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Files.upload/5","doc":"* `:create_dirs` — Create parent directories if they don't exist. Defaults to `true`.","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#upload/5-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Files.write/4","doc":"Writes string or binary content directly to a file on the computer.\n\nConvenience wrapper around `upload/5` for in-memory content.","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#write/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Miosa.Files.write/4","doc":":ok = Miosa.Files.write(client, computer_id, \"/home/user/hello.txt\", \"Hello, world!\")","ref":"Miosa.Files.html#write/4-example"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy","doc":"Read and write the network egress/ingress policy for a MIOSA computer.\n\nA network policy controls which hosts and ports a computer can reach on the\npublic internet. The default policy allows all outbound traffic.","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.NetworkPolicy","doc":"{:ok, policy} = Miosa.NetworkPolicy.get(client, computer_id)\n\n    {:ok, policy} = Miosa.NetworkPolicy.set(client, computer_id, %{\n      rules: [\n        %{direction: \"egress\", action: \"allow\", host: \"api.example.com\", port: 443},\n        %{direction: \"egress\", action: \"deny\",  host: \"*\", port: \"*\"}\n      ]\n    })\n\n    :ok = Miosa.NetworkPolicy.reset(client, computer_id)","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.policy_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html#t:policy_params/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.rule_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html#t:rule_params/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.get/2","doc":"Returns the current network policy for a computer.","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.reset/2","doc":"Resets the network policy to the default (allow all outbound) for a computer.","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html#reset/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.set/3","doc":"Replaces the network policy for a computer.\n\nThe supplied rules fully replace the existing policy.","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html#set/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Params - Miosa.NetworkPolicy.set/3","doc":"* `:rules` — Required. List of rule maps with `:direction`, `:action`,\n    and optionally `:host` and `:port`.","ref":"Miosa.NetworkPolicy.html#set/3-params"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes","doc":"Background process management for a sandbox.\n\nWraps:\n  * `POST   /sandboxes/:id/processes`              — start/4\n  * `GET    /sandboxes/:id/processes`              — list/2\n  * `DELETE /sandboxes/:id/processes/:pid`         — kill/3\n  * `POST   /sandboxes/:id/processes/:pid/stdin`   — send_stdin/4","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.kill/3","doc":"Kill a background process by its PID\n(DELETE `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/processes/:pid`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.html#kill/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.list/2","doc":"List all running background processes in the sandbox\n(GET `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/processes`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.send_stdin/4","doc":"Send data to the stdin of a running background process\n(POST `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/processes/:pid/stdin`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.html#send_stdin/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.start/4","doc":"Start a background process in the sandbox\n(POST `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/processes`).","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.html#start/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options map keys - Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.start/4","doc":"* `\"cwd\"` — Working directory for the process.\n  * `\"env\"` — Environment variables map.\n  * `\"timeout\"` — Process timeout in seconds.","ref":"Miosa.Sandbox.Processes.html#start/4-options-map-keys"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes","doc":"Sandboxes — a thin helper over `Miosa.Computers` that defaults\n`template_type` to `\"miosa-sandbox\"` (ephemeral code-exec rootfs, no\ndesktop).\n\nMirrors the one-resource product model used by E2B and Daytona: the\ncomputer is the single resource type, and `template_type` selects its\nflavour. A sandbox is just a computer with the lightweight template;\nevery other module (`Miosa.Computer`, `Miosa.Exec`, `Miosa.Files`,\n`Miosa.Desktop`) works identically.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Sandboxes","doc":"client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_...\")\n\n    {:ok, sandbox} = Miosa.Sandboxes.create(client, %{name: \"quick-exec\"})\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.start(client, sandbox.id)\n    {:ok, %{output: out}} = Miosa.Exec.run(client, sandbox.id, command: \"echo hi\")\n    :ok = Miosa.Computer.destroy(client, sandbox.id)","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes.create/2","doc":"Create a sandbox — a computer provisioned with the `miosa-sandbox` template.\n\nAccepts the same attributes as `Miosa.Computers.create/2`; the\n`template_type` key defaults to `\"miosa-sandbox\"` when omitted.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"White-label attribution - Miosa.Sandboxes.create/2","doc":"Pass `:external_workspace_id`, `:external_user_id`, `:external_project_id`\nto tag the sandbox with your platform's customer/user/project IDs. These\nfields never authorize anything — tenancy is always derived server-side\nfrom the API key — but they let your list/usage APIs group by attribution.\n\n    {:ok, sandbox} = Miosa.Sandboxes.create(client, %{\n      name: \"smile-dental\",\n      external_workspace_id: \"dental-office-123\",\n      external_user_id: \"dr-smith-456\",\n      external_project_id: \"landing-page-789\"\n    })","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#create/2-white-label-attribution"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes.delete/2","doc":"Destroy a sandbox. Alias for `Miosa.Computers.delete/2`.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes.get/2","doc":"Get a sandbox by ID. Alias for `Miosa.Computers.get/2`.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes.list/1","doc":"List sandboxes — filtered to computers whose `template_type` is\n`\"miosa-sandbox\"`.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes.readiness/2","doc":"Return the readiness-probe state for a sandbox\n(GET `/sandboxes/:sandbox_id/readiness`).\n\nUseful to poll after creation before issuing exec commands.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#readiness/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes.template/0","doc":"Template slug used for the lightweight code-exec sandbox rootfs.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#template/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Sandboxes.wait_until_ready/3","doc":"Block until the sandbox reports ready, or `timeout` seconds elapse.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#wait_until_ready/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Sandboxes.wait_until_ready/3","doc":"* `:timeout` — seconds to wait. Defaults to `30`.\n  * `:stream`  — when `true` (the default) the SDK first attempts the\n    server-side SSE endpoint `GET /sandboxes/:id/readiness/stream` which\n    pushes `event: ready` as soon as the sandbox boots (and immediately if\n    it is already ready). When `false` the SDK only polls.\n\nReturns `{:ok, true}` once ready, `{:ok, false}` on the server-emitted\n`event: timeout` frame or when the local timeout elapses before ready.\n\nIf the SSE endpoint returns 404 (server pre-dates the streaming endpoint)\nthis transparently falls back to polling `readiness/2` every 10 ms.","ref":"Miosa.Sandboxes.html#wait_until_ready/3-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Services","doc":"Manage long-running background services inside a MIOSA computer.\n\nA service is a supervised process (e.g. a web server, a database, a worker)\nthat runs inside the VM and can be started, stopped, restarted, and observed\nvia a log stream.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Services","doc":"{:ok, svc} = Miosa.Services.create(client, computer_id, %{\n      name: \"web\",\n      command: \"python -m http.server 8080\",\n      working_dir: \"/home/user/app\"\n    })\n\n    :ok = Miosa.Services.start(client, computer_id, svc.id)\n    :ok = Miosa.Services.stop(client, computer_id, svc.id)\n    :ok = Miosa.Services.restart(client, computer_id, svc.id)\n\n    # Tail logs as a Stream\n    log_stream = Miosa.Services.logs(client, computer_id, svc.id)\n    Enum.each(log_stream, fn %Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent{line: l} -> IO.puts(l) end)\n\n    :ok = Miosa.Services.delete(client, computer_id, svc.id)","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Services.create_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#t:create_params/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.create/3","doc":"Creates a new service definition inside a computer.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#create/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Params - Miosa.Services.create/3","doc":"* `:name` — Required. Unique name for the service within this computer.\n  * `:command` — Required. Shell command to run.\n  * `:working_dir` — Working directory. Defaults to `\"/home/user\"`.\n  * `:env` — Map of additional environment variables.\n  * `:auto_restart` — Restart on crash. Defaults to `false`.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#create/3-params"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.delete/3","doc":"Deletes a service definition.\n\nThe service must be stopped before deletion.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.get/3","doc":"Fetches a single service by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.list/2","doc":"Lists all services for a computer.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.logs/4","doc":"Returns a `Stream` of `Miosa.Types.ServiceLogEvent` structs for a service.\n\nThe stream tails the service's stdout/stderr in real time via SSE. It\ncompletes when the server closes the connection or the service exits.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#logs/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Miosa.Services.logs/4","doc":"* `:follow` — Continue streaming after the service exits until the\n    connection is closed. Defaults to `true`.\n  * `:tail` — Number of historical lines to include before live output.\n    Defaults to `0` (live only).","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#logs/4-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Miosa.Services.logs/4","doc":"Miosa.Services.logs(client, computer_id, service_id)\n    |> Stream.each(fn %{line: l} -> IO.puts(l) end)\n    |> Stream.run()","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#logs/4-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.restart/3","doc":"Restarts a service (stop + start).","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#restart/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.start/3","doc":"Starts a service.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#start/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Services.stop/3","doc":"Stops a running service.","ref":"Miosa.Services.html#stop/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Workspaces","doc":"Manage MIOSA workspaces.\n\nA workspace groups one or more computers under a shared project boundary.\nWorkspaces are identified by an ID and carry a display name and optional\nmetadata. Every computer belongs to exactly one workspace.","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Miosa.Workspaces","doc":"client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_...\")\n\n    {:ok, ws} = Miosa.Workspaces.create(client, %{name: \"my-project\"})\n    {:ok, workspaces} = Miosa.Workspaces.list(client)\n    {:ok, ws} = Miosa.Workspaces.get(client, ws.id)\n    {:ok, ws} = Miosa.Workspaces.update(client, ws.id, %{name: \"renamed\"})\n    {:ok, computers} = Miosa.Workspaces.list_computers(client, ws.id)\n    :ok = Miosa.Workspaces.delete(client, ws.id)","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.create_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#t:create_params/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.update_params/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#t:update_params/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.create/2","doc":"Creates a new workspace.","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Params - Miosa.Workspaces.create/2","doc":"* `:name` — Required. Display name for the workspace.\n  * `:metadata` — Optional. Arbitrary key-value map.","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#create/2-params"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.delete/2","doc":"Deletes a workspace.\n\nAll computers in the workspace must be stopped or destroyed before deletion,\nor the API will return a 409 conflict.","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.get/2","doc":"Fetches a single workspace by ID.","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.list/1","doc":"Lists all workspaces for the authenticated tenant.","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.list_computers/2","doc":"Lists all computers belonging to a workspace.","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#list_computers/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Workspaces.update/3","doc":"Updates a workspace's attributes.\n\nOnly the supplied fields are updated (PATCH semantics).","ref":"Miosa.Workspaces.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers","doc":"OpenComputers API surface — register and control your own machines via MIOSA.\n\nOpenComputers lets you bring your own Mac, Linux, or Windows machine and\ncontrol it through the MIOSA API: run commands, manage files, expose HTTP\ntunnels, dispatch AI agents, build inference clusters, and manage secrets.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Entry points - Miosa.OpenComputers","doc":"All functions accept a `Miosa.Client.t()` as the first argument:\n\n    client = Miosa.client(\"msk_u_...\")\n\n    # Hosts\n    {:ok, resp} = Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.list(client)\n    {:ok, host} = Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.create(client, %{name: \"my-mac\"})\n\n    # Jobs\n    {:ok, job} = Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.run(client, host[\"id\"], %{command: \"npm test\"})\n\n    # Tunnels\n    {:ok, tunnel} = Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.create(client, host[\"id\"], %{target_port: 3000})\n    IO.puts(tunnel[\"public_url\"])\n\n    # Agents\n    {:ok, session} = Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.dispatch(client, host[\"id\"], %{task: \"run tests\"})","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.html#module-entry-points"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents","doc":"AI agent dispatch for registered hosts.\n\nDispatch an AI agent to autonomously complete a task on your host. The agent\ncan run commands, edit files, browse the web, and more.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.cancel/3","doc":"Cancel a running agent session.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.html#cancel/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.dispatch/3","doc":"Dispatch an AI agent to run a task on the host.\n\n`attrs` must include `:task`. Optional: `:model_id`, `:max_turns`, `:context`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.html#dispatch/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.events/4","doc":"Stream live events from an agent session (SSE).\n\nThe callback receives `%{type: type, data: data}` maps. Blocks until done.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.html#events/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.get/3","doc":"Get a specific agent session.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.list/2","doc":"List agent sessions for a host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Agents.html#list/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters","doc":"Inference cluster management.\n\nA cluster groups multiple registered hosts to serve an LLM model via an\nOpenAI-compatible endpoint at `/inference/{slug}/v1/chat/completions`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.create/2","doc":"Create an inference cluster.\n\n`attrs` must include `:name`, `:model`, `:host_ids`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.delete/2","doc":"Delete a cluster.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.get/2","doc":"Get a specific cluster.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.list/1","doc":"List inference clusters.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.start/2","doc":"Start a stopped cluster.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html#start/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.stop/2","doc":"Stop a running cluster.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Clusters.html#stop/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.DesktopVnc","doc":"Issue WebSocket tickets for desktop (VNC/KasmVNC) sessions on registered hosts.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.DesktopVnc.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.DesktopVnc.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.DesktopVnc.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.DesktopVnc.ticket/2","doc":"Issue a short-lived WebSocket ticket for a desktop session.\n\nConnect immediately to `ws_url` using the returned `ticket`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.DesktopVnc.html#ticket/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs","doc":"Remote file system operations on registered hosts.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.delete/3","doc":"Delete a file or directory on the host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.download/3","doc":"Download a file as binary.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html#download/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.list/3","doc":"List directory entries at `remote_path`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html#list/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.mkdir/3","doc":"Create a directory (and all parents) on the host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html#mkdir/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.stat/3","doc":"Stat a path (size, mode, is_dir, symlink, etc.).","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html#stat/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.upload/5","doc":"Upload `content` (binary) to `remote_path` on the host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Fs.html#upload/5"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts","doc":"Host registration and lifecycle.\n\nA **host** is a physical or virtual machine you own that has been registered\nwith MIOSA by installing the `miosa-host` agent. Once registered, MIOSA can\ndispatch jobs, manage files, issue tunnels, and run AI agents on it.\n\nThe `host_key` is returned **only on creation** — save it immediately.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.create/2","doc":"Register a new host.\n\n`attrs` must include `:name`. Optional: `:region`, `:labels`.\n\nThe returned map includes `host_key` — shown **once**, store it securely.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.events/3","doc":"Stream live host events (SSE).\n\nThe `callback` is called for each `%{type: type, data: data}` event map.\nBlocks until the stream ends. Returns `:ok` or `{:error, reason}`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html#events/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.get/2","doc":"Get a host by ID.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.list/2","doc":"List all registered hosts.\n\nOptions: `:page`, `:per_page`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.revoke/2","doc":"Revoke a host registration. The host loses access immediately.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html#revoke/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.update/3","doc":"Update host metadata (name, labels).","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Hosts.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs","doc":"Remote job execution on registered hosts.\n\nJobs dispatch shell commands to a registered host and return the result once\nthe command completes.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.cancel/3","doc":"Cancel a running job.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.html#cancel/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.get/3","doc":"Get a specific job by ID.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.list/3","doc":"List jobs for a host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.html#list/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.run/3","doc":"Run a command on a host and return the completed job.\n\n`attrs` must include `:command`. Optional: `:args`, `:env`, `:cwd`, `:timeout`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.html#run/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.stream/4","doc":"Stream live output events from a running job (SSE).\n\nThe callback receives `%{type: type, data: data}` maps. Blocks until done.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Jobs.html#stream/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets","doc":"Encrypted secret management for OpenComputers.\n\nSecrets can be scoped to the whole tenant or to a specific host. The secret\nvalue is encrypted at rest and injected as environment variables on the host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.create/2","doc":"Create a tenant-scoped secret.\n\n`attrs` must include `:name` and `:value`. Optional: `:description`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.create_for_host/3","doc":"Create a secret scoped to a specific host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#create_for_host/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.delete/2","doc":"Delete a tenant-scoped secret.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.delete_for_host/3","doc":"Delete a host-scoped secret.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#delete_for_host/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.list/1","doc":"List tenant-scoped secrets.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#list/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.list_for_host/2","doc":"List secrets scoped to a specific host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#list_for_host/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.update/3","doc":"Update a tenant-scoped secret.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Secrets.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Terminal","doc":"Issue WebSocket tickets for terminal sessions on registered hosts.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Terminal.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Terminal.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Terminal.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Terminal.ticket/2","doc":"Issue a short-lived WebSocket ticket for a terminal session.\n\nConnect immediately to `ws_url` using the returned `ticket`. The ticket\nexpires in a few seconds.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Terminal.html#ticket/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels","doc":"HTTP tunnel management for registered hosts.\n\nTunnels expose a local port on the host over a MIOSA-managed public URL.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.result/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.create/3","doc":"Create an HTTP tunnel exposing a local port on the host.\n\n`attrs` must include `:target_port`. Optional: `:auth_mode`, `:slug`.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.html#create/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.delete/3","doc":"Delete a tunnel.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.html#delete/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.get/3","doc":"Get a specific tunnel.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.list/2","doc":"List all tunnels for a host.","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.html#list/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.update/4","doc":"Update a tunnel (port, auth mode, enabled flag).","ref":"Miosa.OpenComputers.Tunnels.html#update/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Miosa.Types","doc":"Typed structs representing all MIOSA API response objects.\n\nAll structs use atom keys and provide a `from_map/1` constructor that\naccepts the raw string-keyed maps returned by the API.","ref":"Miosa.Types.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Types.visibility/0","doc":"Controls who can access a computer's HTTP endpoints.","ref":"Miosa.Types.html#t:visibility/0"},{"type":"exception","title":"Miosa.Error","doc":"Exception raised for MIOSA API errors.\n\nCovers both HTTP-level errors (4xx, 5xx) and client-level errors\n(network failures, JSON decode errors, invalid configuration).","ref":"Miosa.Error.html"},{"type":"exception","title":"Fields - Miosa.Error","doc":"* `:message` — Human-readable error description.\n  * `:status` — HTTP status code (integer), or `nil` for non-HTTP errors.\n  * `:code` — Machine-readable error code string from the API (e.g. `\"INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS\"`), or `nil`.\n  * `:body` — Raw response body map, when available.","ref":"Miosa.Error.html#module-fields"},{"type":"exception","title":"Examples - Miosa.Error","doc":"iex> raise Miosa.Error, message: \"Not found\", status: 404, code: \"NOT_FOUND\"\n    ** (Miosa.Error) [404] NOT_FOUND: Not found","ref":"Miosa.Error.html#module-examples"},{"type":"type","title":"Miosa.Error.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Miosa.Error.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Error.from_exception/1","doc":"Builds a `Miosa.Error` for non-HTTP failures (network errors, decode errors).","ref":"Miosa.Error.html#from_exception/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Miosa.Error.from_response/1","doc":"Builds a `Miosa.Error` from a `Req.Response` struct.\n\nParses the JSON body for `\"error\"` and `\"code\"` keys following the\nMIOSA API error envelope format.","ref":"Miosa.Error.html#from_response/1"},{"type":"extras","title":"miosa (Elixir)","doc":"# miosa (Elixir)\n\n> Official Elixir SDK for MIOSA — the AI cloud platform for sandboxes, computers, deployments, and managed data.\n\n[![Hex version](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/miosa.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/miosa)\n[![Hex downloads](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/dt/miosa.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/miosa)\n[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)\n[![Docs](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-hexdocs.pm%2Fmiosa-blue)](https://hexdocs.pm/miosa)\n\nElixir 1.15+. HTTP transport via `Req`, JSON via `Jason`.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Install - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:miosa, \"~> 1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nThen run `mix deps.get`.","ref":"readme.html#install"},{"type":"extras","title":"Quickstart - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\nclient = Miosa.client(\"msk_live_...\")\n\n{:ok, computer} = Miosa.Computers.create(client, %{\n  name: \"my-build\",\n  template_type: \"miosa-sandbox\",\n  size: \"small\"\n})\n\n{:ok, result} = Miosa.Exec.bash(client, computer.id, \"echo 'hello from miosa'\")\nIO.puts(result.output)  # hello from miosa\n\n{:ok, _} = Miosa.Files.write_file(client, computer.id, \"/workspace/app.exs\", ~s(IO.puts(\"hi\")))\n{:ok, text} = Miosa.Files.read_file(client, computer.id, \"/workspace/app.exs\")\n\n:ok = Miosa.Computers.delete(client, computer.id)\n```","ref":"readme.html#quickstart"},{"type":"extras","title":"What's included - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"| Module | Description |\n|---|---|\n| **Computers** | |\n| `Miosa.Computers` | Create, list, get, update, delete computers |\n| `Miosa.Computer` | Bound handle — start, stop, restart, clone, resize, wait |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Agent` | CUA sessions — run, list, get, cancel AI agent sessions |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Env` | Per-computer environment variables |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Logs` | Computer log retrieval + SSE streaming |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Metrics` | CPU/memory metrics |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Ports` | Port mapping CRUD |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Terminal` | PTY session create + resize |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Volumes` | Attach/detach volumes to computers |\n| `Miosa.Computer.AutoStop` | Auto-stop timer get/update |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Inbox` | Computer inbox get/update |\n| `Miosa.Computer.Osa` | OSA agent task submit/cancel/configure |\n| **Desktop** | |\n| `Miosa.Desktop` | Screenshot, click, double_click, right_click, type, key, hotkey, scroll, drag, move, launch, windows, cursor, focus_window |\n| **Exec & Files** | |\n| `Miosa.Exec` | `bash/4`, `python/4`, `spawn/4` execution inside VMs |\n| `Miosa.Exec.Command` | WebSocket PTY — send_stdin, resize, await |\n| `Miosa.Files` | Upload, download, write, read, list, stat, mkdir, rename, copy, chmod, delete, export |\n| **Sandboxes** | |\n| `Miosa.Sandboxes` | Create, list, get, delete sandboxes + wait_until_ready |\n| `Miosa.Sandbox.Processes` | Background process start/list/kill/send_stdin |\n| `Miosa.Sandbox.Events` | SSE event streaming + file watch |\n| `Miosa.Sandbox.Previews` | Preview URL create/list/share/revoke |\n| `Miosa.Sandbox.Terminal` | Sandbox PTY session create/delete |\n| `Miosa.Sandbox.Env` | Sandbox environment variables |\n| `Miosa.Sandbox.Tags` | Sandbox tag management |\n| `Miosa.SandboxTemplates` | Template CRUD + builds |\n| **Deployments** | |\n| `Miosa.Deployments` | Create, list, publish, rollback, versions, releases, builds, env, domains, runtime instances |\n| **Data** | |\n| `Miosa.Databases` | Create, list, get, delete, start/stop/restart, credentials, logs |\n| `Miosa.Storage` | Buckets CRUD + objects put/get/delete/list + presign |\n| `Miosa.Volumes` | Volume CRUD |\n| **Platform** | |\n| `Miosa.Functions` | Edge functions CRUD + invoke |\n| `Miosa.Webhooks` | Webhook CRUD + test + deliveries |\n| `Miosa.CronJobs` | Cron job CRUD + pause/resume/run_now + executions |\n| `Miosa.ApiKeys` | API key CRUD |\n| `Miosa.Workspaces` | Workspace CRUD + list_computers |\n| `Miosa.CustomDomains` | Custom domain register/verify/delete |\n| `Miosa.NetworkPolicy` | Network policy get/set/reset |\n| `Miosa.Services` | Service CRUD + start/stop/restart/logs |\n| `Miosa.Checkpoints` | Snapshot create/list/restore/delete |\n| `Miosa.Events` | SSE event streaming per computer |\n| `Miosa.Settings` | Platform settings + branding |\n| `Miosa.Credits` | Credit balance + transactions |\n| `Miosa.Completions` | Chat/text completions + SSE streaming |\n| `Miosa.Regions` | Available regions |\n| **BYOC & Admin** | |\n| `Miosa.OpenComputers` | BYOC host management (hosts, jobs, tunnels, agents, clusters, secrets) |\n| `Miosa.Admin` | Admin-scoped operations (dashboard, users, tenants, credits, plans) |","ref":"readme.html#what-s-included"},{"type":"extras","title":"Exec - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, result} = Miosa.Exec.bash(client, computer.id, \"ls -la /workspace\",\n  timeout: 10_000,\n  working_dir: \"/workspace\",\n  env: %{\"DEBUG\" => \"1\"}\n)\nIO.puts(result.stdout)\nIO.puts(\"exit: #{result.exit_code}\")\n\n{:ok, py} = Miosa.Exec.python(client, computer.id, \"\"\"\n  import json\n  print(json.dumps({\"status\": \"ok\"}))\n\"\"\")\nIO.puts(py.output)\n```","ref":"readme.html#exec"},{"type":"extras","title":"File operations - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\n# Write / read\n{:ok, _} = Miosa.Files.write_file(client, id, \"/workspace/app.py\", \"print('hi')\")\n{:ok, text} = Miosa.Files.read_file(client, id, \"/workspace/app.py\")\n\n# Upload binary\n{:ok, _} = Miosa.Files.upload(client, id, \"./local.txt\", \"/workspace/remote.txt\")\n\n# List / stat / mkdir / rename / delete\n{:ok, entries} = Miosa.Files.list(client, id, \"/workspace\")\n{:ok, stat}    = Miosa.Files.stat(client, id, \"/workspace/app.py\")\n{:ok, _}       = Miosa.Files.mkdir(client, id, \"/workspace/output\")\n{:ok, _}       = Miosa.Files.rename(client, id, \"/workspace/old.py\", \"/workspace/new.py\")\n:ok            = Miosa.Files.delete(client, id, \"/workspace/old.py\")\n```","ref":"readme.html#file-operations"},{"type":"extras","title":"Desktop control - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, png} = Miosa.Desktop.screenshot(client, computer.id)\nFile.write!(\"screen.png\", png)\n\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.click(client, computer.id, 640, 400)\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.double_click(client, computer.id, 640, 400)\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.right_click(client, computer.id, 640, 400)\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.type(client, computer.id, \"hello world\")\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.key(client, computer.id, \"Return\")\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.key(client, computer.id, \"ctrl+c\")\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.scroll(client, computer.id, 640, 400, \"down\", 3)\n:ok = Miosa.Desktop.drag(client, computer.id, 100, 100, 400, 400)\n\n{:ok, windows} = Miosa.Desktop.windows(client, computer.id)\n{:ok, cursor}  = Miosa.Desktop.cursor(client, computer.id)\n:ok            = Miosa.Desktop.launch(client, computer.id, \"firefox\")\n```","ref":"readme.html#desktop-control"},{"type":"extras","title":"SSE event streaming - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\n:ok = Miosa.Events.stream(client, computer.id, fn event ->\n  IO.inspect({event.type, event.data})\nend)\n```","ref":"readme.html#sse-event-streaming"},{"type":"extras","title":"OTP / Supervisor integration - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\nchildren = [\n  {Miosa.Client, api_key: System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\")}\n]\n\nSupervisor.start_link(children, strategy: :one_for_one)\n```","ref":"readme.html#otp-supervisor-integration"},{"type":"extras","title":"Phoenix / LiveView integration - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyAppWeb.SandboxLive do\n  use Phoenix.LiveView\n\n  def mount(_params, _session, socket) do\n    client = Miosa.client(System.fetch_env!(\"MIOSA_API_KEY\"))\n    {:ok, assign(socket, client: client, output: nil)}\n  end\n\n  def handle_event(\"run\", %{\"cmd\" => cmd}, socket) do\n    {:ok, result} = Miosa.Exec.bash(\n      socket.assigns.client,\n      socket.assigns.computer_id,\n      cmd\n    )\n    {:noreply, assign(socket, output: result.output)}\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#phoenix-liveview-integration"},{"type":"extras","title":"White-label / multi-tenant - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, computer} = Miosa.Computers.create(client, %{\n  name: \"customer-build\",\n  template_type: \"miosa-sandbox\",\n  metadata: %{\n    \"external_workspace_id\" => \"acme-corp\",\n    \"external_user_id\"      => \"user-99\"\n  }\n})\n```","ref":"readme.html#white-label-multi-tenant"},{"type":"extras","title":"Error handling - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"All functions return `{:ok, result}` or `{:error, %Miosa.Error{}}`:\n\n```elixir\ncase Miosa.Computers.get(client, \"cmp_doesnt_exist\") do\n  {:ok, computer} ->\n    computer\n\n  {:error, %Miosa.Error{status: 404}} ->\n    IO.puts(\"not found\")\n\n  {:error, %Miosa.Error{status: 429, message: msg}} ->\n    IO.puts(\"rate limited: #{msg}\")\n\n  {:error, %Miosa.Error{message: msg}} ->\n    IO.puts(\"error: #{msg}\")\nend\n```\n\n`Miosa.Error` fields: `:message`, `:status`, `:code`, `:body`.","ref":"readme.html#error-handling"},{"type":"extras","title":"Configuration - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"```elixir\nclient = Miosa.client(\"msk_live_...\",\n  base_url:        \"https://api.miosa.ai/api/v1\",\n  timeout:         30_000,\n  receive_timeout: 60_000,\n  retry:           false\n)\n```\n\n| Option | Default |\n|---|---|\n| `:api_key` | required — pass explicitly; env var not auto-read |\n| `:base_url` | `https://api.miosa.ai/api/v1` |\n| `:timeout` | `30_000` ms |\n| `:receive_timeout` | `60_000` ms |\n| `:retry` | `false` |","ref":"readme.html#configuration"},{"type":"extras","title":"Links - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"- [HexDocs reference](https://hexdocs.pm/miosa)\n- [Full documentation](https://miosa.ai/docs/sdks/elixir)\n- [Quickstart](https://miosa.ai/docs/quickstart)\n- [GitHub](https://github.com/Miosa-osa/miosa-elixir)\n- [Contact](mailto:platform@miosa.ai)","ref":"readme.html#links"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - miosa (Elixir)","doc":"MIT","ref":"readme.html#license"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}